//fell_down_well_event.nut
	text = text.replace("A woman jumps out of the treeline beside the path.", "一个女人从小路旁边的树林里跳出来。");
	text = text.replace("Oh thank the gods, my prayers have been answered!", "噢，感谢上帝，我的祈祷应验了！");
	text = text.replace("Please, come quick! My grandpap has fallen down the well!", "请，快过来！我爷爷掉到井里了！");
	text = text.replace(/She turns and hurries away as though you\'ve already agreed to help her. (.*?) glances at you and shrugs\./, "她转身匆匆离去，好像你已经答应帮她了。$1 瞥了你一眼，并耸耸肩。");
	
	text = text.replace("You decide it\'s worth your time and go and take a look.", "你觉得值得花时间去看看。");
	text = text.replace("The old man was doing repairs on the wellhead, a wooden framework meant to cover its opening, when it broke apart and sent him plunging down.", "老人正在修理井口，那是一个用来盖住井口的木制框架，但是破损了一部分，使老人跌落井中。");
	text = text.replace("Staring into the well, you find the man staring back up.", "盯着井里，你发现那个老人也盯着你。");
	text = text.replace("He gives a wave.", "他挥了挥手。");
	text = text.replace("Oy\' there, fellas. I\'m in a bit of a pickle.", "啊，这里，伙计们。我有点麻烦。");
	text = text.replace("I\'m actually being pickled, now that I think about it...", "我确实糗了，我现在还在寻思…");
	text = text.replace(/Eh, right\. (.*?) throws down a rope and the old man ties it around himself\./, "嗯,对的。$1 扔下一根绳子，老人把它系在自己身上。");
	text = text.replace("You and the sellsword pull the woman\'s grandfather up and back onto dry land.", "你和佣兵把女人的爷爷拉上地面。");
	text = text.replace("He shakes your hand and thanks you cordially.", "他和你握手，衷心地感谢你。");
	text = text.replace("Farkin\' hell, glad you came when you did, I was about to shit and piss like no other.", "他妈的，真高兴你来帮忙，我差点大小便失禁了。");
	text = text.replace("Let me tell ya, this ain\'t my first time going down a well.", "让我告诉你，这不是我第一次下井。");
	text = text.replace("Five years ago I\'d done it while repairing the wellhead, because the wellhead breaks often, you see.", "五年前我就干修理井口这个活了，因为井口经常破裂，你知道的。");
	text = text.replace("And it\'s not really a wellhead, we just call it that cause we\'re lazy.", "它不是真正的井口，我们叫它井口是因为我们很懒。");
	text = text.replace("Back in my day we called it a... well, heh well, I actually done forgot.", "那时候我们叫它…好吧，很好，我真的忘了。");
	text = text.replace("I guess a \'wellhead\' makes sense now, as I\'m not well in the head!", "我想现在一个“井口”是有意义的，因为我的脑袋不舒服！");
	text = text.replace("Ho! Still got it.", "喂！还有它。");
	text = text.replace("I was quite the charmer in my days, you see, and it\'s not often I get to put the practice in.", "我当年可真有魅力，你看，我很少有机会练习。");
	text = text.replace("M\'wife died ten years ago, and the one prior to her left me twenty winters ago!", "我的妻子十年前就去世了，而上一个老婆二十年前就离开了我！");
	text = text.replace("I say winters, because that\'s when she left me, in the winter.", "我说的是冬天，因为那是她离开我的时候，在冬天。");
	text = text.replace("It was a brutal one and I had asked her to help chop the wood lest we all freeze.", "那是一个残酷的时刻，我让她帮忙砍柴，免得我们都冻僵了。");
	text = text.replace("She said she wasn\'t doing that shit and taking care of the kids at the same time.", "她说她不会一边照顾孩子一边干那些蠢事。");
	text = text.replace("I had kids with her as well as with the second wife.", "我和她还有第二个妻子都有孩子。");
	text = text.replace("Five total. One died. Measles.", "一共五个。一个死了。死于麻疹。");
	text = text.replace("Another disappeared, so he\'s probably dead.", "另一个失踪了，所以他可能已经死了。");
	text = text.replace("I try to be honest to myself about it, but you know, there\'s hope.", "我试着让自己诚实，但你知道，还是有希望的。");
	text = text.replace("If a random stranger can be found in the forest to save me in the nick of time, then maybe my son survived that battle with the greenskins.", "如果在关键时刻能在森林里找到一个陌生人来救我，那么也许我的儿子能在与绿皮的战斗中幸存了下来。");
	text = text.replace("Ain\'t heard of him, though.", "不过我没有他的消息了。");
	text = text.replace("I pray to the old gods and even that Davkul fella every now and again.", "我不时地向古老神明们祈祷，甚至向那个达库尔祈祷。");
	text = text.replace("Do you know of Davkul?", "你知道达库尔？");
	text = text.replace("I\'m not sure what to make of it.", "我不知道这是怎么回事。");
	text = text.replace("One time this man came by with a scar on his forehead, said he\'d show me the way of darkness.", "有一次，一个额头上有一道伤疤的人从我身边走过，他说他会给我指点黑暗之路。");
	text = text.replace("I said I see darkness everytime I nap.", "我说我每次小睡都会看到黑暗。");
	text = text.replace("This scarred fella said one day I won\'t wake and I said good! Ha!", "这个伤痕累累的家伙说有一天我不会醒来，我说很好！哈！");
	text = text.replace("So then this scarred bastard starts getting upset with me...", "然后这个伤痕累累的混蛋就开始生我的气…");
	text = text.replace(/As he drones on, you look around for (.*?) only to find him stepping out of the woman\'s home, the lady herself carrying a bit of\.\.\. obvious warmth on her face\./, "当他喋喋不休的时候，你四处寻找 $1，却发现他从女人的家里走了出来，女人自己也带着一点…她脸上有明显的红晕。");
	text = text.replace("You retrieve your sellsword and leave before the old man lops your head with the most longwinded and one-sided conversation ever.", "你召回你的佣兵，在老头子用最冗长、单调的谈话砍掉你的脑袋之前离开。");
	
	text = text.replace("The old man was doing repairs atop the wooden wellhead when it broke apart.", "当木制井口破裂时，老人正在修理。");
	text = text.replace("Unfortunately, if you\'re standing atop a wellhead when it goes bust there\'s only one place to go: down.", "不幸的是，当井口破裂时，如果你站在井口上，只有一个地方可以去：向下。");
	text = text.replace("Very, very far down.", "非常，非常深。");
	text = text.replace(/As you look over the edge of the well, you can see the old man floating in a matter that is most unlively\. (.*?) sidles up next to you and whispers, using a hand to keep his words from being heard\./, "当你从井的边缘往下看时，你可以看到老人正漂浮，在某种意义上说已经没命了。$1 悄悄靠近你，用手捂着嘴，不让别人听见他说的话。");
	text = text.replace("Uh, he\'s not moving.", "呃，他不动了。");
	text = text.replace("An expertly observation, truly.", "这是一个非常专业的观察。");
	text = text.replace("You inform the lady of the man\'s passing.", "你把老人的死告诉那位女士。");
	text = text.replace("She purses her lips and asks that you remove the body anyway, explaning her reasoning rather succinctly.", "她噘起嘴唇，让你们把尸体清理掉，并直截了当地解释了她的理由。");
	text = text.replace("We can\'t be drinking his filth after all.", "我们毕竟不能喝他的尸水。");
	text = text.replace(/Fair enough\. (.*?) manages to hook a rope-loop around the corpse and pull it up, its limbs dangling loosely like white washrags\./, "足够正确。$1 设法用绳子把尸体吊起来，它的四肢像白毛巾一样松散地垂着。");
	text = text.replace("He asks if she needs you to bury it, too.", "他问她是否也需要你把它埋了。");
	text = text.replace("The woman wipes a tear and shakes her head.", "那个女人擦了擦眼泪，摇了摇头。");
	text = text.replace("Nah. I\'ll bury that feller myself, weep over his grave tomorrow, and then get on with living.", "不。我要亲自埋葬他，明天还要去哭坟，然后继续生活。");
	
	text = text.replace("You decide it\'s worth your time and go and take a look.", "你觉得值得花时间去看看。");
	text = text.replace("The wellhead, a wooden framework meant to cover its opening, has broken apart.", "井口是一个用来盖住井口的木制框架，现在已经破裂。");
	text = text.replace("Apparently, the old man was doing repairs atop it when this happened and so he plunged down into the well.", "很明显，老人当时正在修理，所以他跌落进了井里。");
	text = text.replace("He looks up at you.", "他抬头看着你。");
	text = text.replace("Oy\' there, fellas. I\'m in a bit of a pickle.", "啊，这里，伙计们。我有点麻烦。");
	text = text.replace("I\'m actually being pickled now that I think about it...", "我确实糗了，我现在还在寻思…");
	text = text.replace(/Eh, right\. (.*?) throws down a rope\./, "嗯，对的。$1 系下一根绳子。");
	text = text.replace("The old man ties it around himself.", "老人把它绑在自己身上。");
	text = text.replace("You and the sellsword pull the woman\'s grandfather up and back onto dry land.", "你和佣兵把女人的爷爷拉上地面。");
	text = text.replace("He shakes your hand and thanks you cordially.", "他和你握手，衷心地感谢你。");
	text = text.replace("Farkin\' hell, glad you came when you did, I was about to shit and piss like no other.", "他妈的，真高兴你来帮忙，我差点大小便失禁了。");
	text = text.replace("You talk with the old fella for a time, learning a lot about him.", "你和那个老家伙聊了一会儿，了解了他的很多情况。");
	text = text.replace(/A while later, you realize (.*?) is nowhere in sight\./, "过了一会儿，你意识到 $1 不见了。");
	text = text.replace("Just as you think to start looking for him he steps out of the woman\'s home.", "就在你想开始找他的时候，他从女人的家里走了出来。");
	text = text.replace("She\'s glomming onto his muscles and being rather touchy feely.", "她紧贴着他的胸肌，一阵卿卿我我。");

//fish_caught_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/While stopped near a river of water, it appears (.*?) went out to practice his old trade and netted a few fish!/, "在一条河边停了下来时，看来 $1 要去干他的老本行并抓到了几条鱼！");
	text = text.replace(/You\'ve come to a body of water and stopped to talk to a few locals about the surrounding land\. (.*?) the once-fisherman took that opportunity to go catch a few salmon and other river-running critters\./, "你来到一片水域，停下来和几个当地人谈论周围的风土人情。$1 这个曾经的渔夫抓住机会去逮了几条大马哈鱼和其他水生动物。");
	text = text.replace(/While marching near a river, (.*?) the once-fisherman managed to run along the banks and collect a bucketful of crawdads!/, "在沿河行军的时候，$1 这个曾经的渔夫，沿着河岸奔跑并抓了一桶龙虾！");
	text = text.replace("Boiled in a pot, they make for some good eats.", "放在锅里煮，可以做成美味的食物。");

//fisherman_tells_story_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/(.*?), the ol\' fisherman, regals the company with tales of his fishing days\./, "$1，这个老渔夫，向战队讲述他打鱼的故事。");
	text = text.replace("T\'was this big.", "那条鱼很大。");
	text = text.replace("I swear on me mum!", "我以我妈的名义发誓！");
	text = text.replace("Fish so big that when I yanked it from the waters the whole river dried a foot!", "鱼太大了，当我把它从水里拽出来时，整条河都干枯到一只脚那么浅。");
	text = text.replace("The ocean is a beast, aye, and the skies above its master, the winds its leash, and we men the fleas.", "海洋是一只野兽，是啊，天空是它的主人，风是它的缰绳，而我们人类就是跳蚤。");
	text = text.replace("Lost I was! A summer adrift, the whole boat run through with hunting waters, each wave having taken a sailor for itself until only I remained, aye, aye!", "我迷路了！整个夏天都在海上漂流，整个船在危机四伏的水中穿行，每个浪都带走了一个水手，直到只剩下我一个人，是啊，是啊！");
	text = text.replace("Tis the truth! By autumn, I saw land again, and so happy I was to see the trees and the mountains and the birds that dwell above both that I smashed my ship right into the rocks and kissed the sands as debris drifted about me.", "这是真的！到了秋天，我又看到了陆地，看到树，看到山，看到鸟在上面栖息，我是如此的高兴，以至于我把船撞到岩石上，当碎片在我周围漂浮时，我亲吻着沙滩。");
	text = text.replace("T\'was the happiest day of m\'life.", "这是我一生中最快乐的一天。");
	text = text.replace("Never seen a great white whale before, but a green one?", "以前从没见过大白鲸，但见过一只绿的？");
	text = text.replace("Aye. Wore a coat of moss, a stolen land fur if nothing else.", "是这么回事。穿着一件苔藓外套，不只用什么途径偷来的陆地皮毛。");
	text = text.replace("We hunted it down with spears and ol\' sailor spirit.", "我们用长矛和老水手精神捕猎它。");
	text = text.replace(/Alas, it realized we were on it when (.*?) - a man with the finest harpoon aim there is - struck it in the blowhole\./, "唉，它意识到我们在喷水孔上，当$1－一个人用最锋利的鱼叉瞄准它－把它射到喷水孔里。");
	text = text.replace("I did not know a whale could turn \'round so quickly, but it did, and it made short work of our ship and drowned a number of sailors in a fit of vengenace.", "我不知道一条鲸竟能这样快地掉头，但它做到了，它很快就追上了我们的船，并在一阵狂怒中淹死了许多水手。");
	text = text.replace("I once caught a bass about, yeigh, big.", "我曾经钓到一条鲈鱼，真他妈，大个。");
	text = text.replace("Can you believe that?", "你能相信吗？");
	text = text.replace("Alright, it was this big.", "好吧，它有这么大。");
	text = text.replace("Okay, maybe this big.", "好吧，也许这么大。");
	text = text.replace("Alright I\'ve never caught a bass.", "好吧，我从没钓到过一条鲈鱼。");
	text = text.replace("Fine! I\'ve never even seen a bass!", "好啊！我从来没见过一条鲈鱼！");
	text = text.replace("I just know they\'re out there!", "我只知道它们就在那里！");
	text = text.replace("Leave me alone you land lovers!", "让我自己待会儿，你们这些旱鸭子！");
	text = text.replace("I fish the big seas, dammit!", "我在大海里捕鱼，他妈的！");
	text = text.replace("I know nothing of your silly ponds.", "我对你那些愚蠢的池塘一无所知。");
	text = text.replace("Except bass, of course, I know about them.", "当然，鲈鱼除外，我了解他们。");

//fisherman_vs_farmer_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) and (.*?) are having a bit of an arm-wrestling contest\./, "$1 和 $2 正在进行一场扳手腕比赛。");
	text = text.replace("It\'s all in good fun, having apparently been borne out of an argument on whether fishermen or farmers are more important or whose food is best, that which walks the land or that which swims the oceans.", "这一切都是很有趣的，显然是由一场关于渔夫和农夫谁更重要，谁的食物最好，谁在陆地上行走，谁在海洋里游泳的争论产生的。");
	text = text.replace(/With a long, salty belch, and singing with praise for some long-lost whale, the fisherman puts the last of his strength into the bout and pins (.*?)\'s arm\./, "渔夫打了一个带咸味的长嗝，并为一些失踪已久的鲸唱起了赞歌，他用尽最后一点力气，压倒了 $1的手臂。");
	text = text.replace("Both men get up and clap one another on the shoulders.", "两个人都站起来，拍拍彼此的肩膀。");
	
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) and (.*?) are having a bit of an arm-wrestling contest\./, "$1 和 $2 正在进行一场扳手腕比赛。");
	text = text.replace("It\'s all in good fun, having apparently been borne out of an argument on whether fishermen or farmers are more important or whose food is best or some such thing.", "这一切都是很有趣的，显然是由一场关于渔夫和农夫哪个更重要，谁的食物最好之类的争论产生的。");
	text = text.replace("With a long retelling of the history of his fathers tilling the soils of the land, (.*?) puts the last of his strength into pinning （.*)\'s arm.", "随着对他父亲耕种土地历史的长篇大论，$1 把最后的力气都用在了压住 $2 的手臂上。");
	text = text.replace("Both men get up and clap one another on the shoulders.", "两个人都站起来，拍拍彼此的肩膀。");

//flagellant_vs_monk_event.nut
	text = text.replace("The campfire shines bright, twisting the faces of men in flowing orange as though they themselves were of burning stock.", "营火闪耀着耀眼的光芒，照耀着那些身着鲜艳橙色衣服者的面庞，仿佛他们自己就是燃烧着的木头。");
	text = text.replace(/It is here you find (.*?) and (.*?) talking to one another\./, "就是在这里，你发现 $1 和 $2 相互交谈。");
	text = text.replace("Their discussion is, at first, an easy one.", "他们的讨论的是，一个很简单的事。");
	text = text.replace("The monk pleads with the flagellant to set aside his whip.", "僧侣恳求苦修者把鞭子放下。");
	text = text.replace("While you don\'t necessarily wish to step in, you can\'t help but agree that destroying your own body on a glorified gore-schedule is not the best way to live.", "虽然你没必要介入，但你不得不承认，用一种被美化的仪式摧残自己的身体并不是最好的生活方式。");
	text = text.replace("But then the flagellant retorts with something that gives you both pause.", "但是随后苦修者用一些话来反驳，让你们两个人停了下来。");
	text = text.replace("It is a phrase so well crafted that to think it might justify the man\'s personal habits has you pushing the notion out of your head as fast as possible.", "这是一个精心设计的短语，如果你认为它可以证明这家伙的个人习惯是正确的，你就会尽可能快地把这个概念从你的头脑中踢出去。");
	text = text.replace("Disturbing, too, was the ease with which he said it.", "非常的让人不安，这家伙说的太轻描淡写了。");
	text = text.replace("That such a soothing voice could be so warmly bundled in that scarred husk of flesh.", "如此抚慰人心的声音竟能温暖地裹在伤痕累累的躯壳里。");
	text = text.replace("What could muster it?", "什么造就了它？");
	text = text.replace("The monk stammers for a moment, but then puts his hands to the flagellant\'s shoulders, holding him to keep their eyes on one another.", "这个僧侣结结巴巴地说了一会儿，然后把手放到了那个被鞭笞的人的肩膀上，按着他，让他们互相对视。");
	text = text.replace("He whispers, words which tickle your ears, but don\'t pronounce themselves loud enough to have real meaning.", "他轻声细语，这些话会让你耳朵发痒，但却不会大声地说出它们的真正含义。");
	text = text.replace("You can only assume they are meant to, once again, persuade the flagellant to a better, less violent life.", "你只能假设，他们的目的是，再次说服苦修者过上更好，更少暴力的生活。");
	text = text.replace("But, again, the flagellant begins to respond and so back and forth they continue to go.", "但是，再一次的，苦修者开始回应，然后他们继续开始辩论。");
	
	text = text.replace("Deciding to let the men talk, you step away for a time.", "决定让他俩继续讨论，你走开了一段时间。");
	text = text.replace("When you return, you find the flagellant sitting next to the monk.", "当你回来的时候，你发现苦修者坐在僧侣旁边。");
	text = text.replace("The two saw back and forth on a log, their hands clasped in prayer as whispers of heavenly words part their lips.", "两个人在一根圆木上来回地看了看，双手合十，祈祷着，低声说着神圣的话语，张开了嘴唇。");
	text = text.replace("You\'ve no urge to get closer to hear what they are saying for it is a comforting sight in and of itself.", "你没有必要去听他们在说什么，因为这本身就是一个令人欣慰的景象。");
	text = text.replace("While you have no dog in what way is best to appease the gods, you can\'t help but feel a little better seeing the flagellant put down his tools of self-torture.", "当你对如何侍奉神明不以为然的时候，你会不由自主地感到一丝欣慰，因为苦修者放下了折磨自己的工具。");
	
	text = text.replace("Deciding to let the men talk, you step away for a time.", "决定让他俩继续讨论，你走开了一段时间。");
	text = text.replace("When you come back, the monk is naked and bent over with tears in his eyes.", "你回来的时候，僧侣光着身子，眼里含着泪水。");
	text = text.replace("His shape is craven, but his face is gutting as though this is always what he wanted.", "他的体型像个懦夫，但是面色坚毅，仿佛这就是他想要的。");
	text = text.replace("With a gulp of air he straightens up and flicks his wrist over his shoulder.", "他吸了一口气，直起身子，把手腕甩过肩膀。");
	text = text.replace("The flagellant\'s whip is in hand and you hear the leather slap against the monk\'s back.", "苦修者的鞭子握在手里，你听到皮鞭打在僧侣背上的声音。");
	text = text.replace("He pulls the tool away and the sound of glass and barbs tearing flesh causes a ringing in your ears.", "他把鞭子衰远，鞭刃和倒刺撕裂血肉的声音在你耳中回响。");
	text = text.replace("The flagellant himself says nothing.", "苦修者自己什么也没说。");
	text = text.replace("He has set himself down by the monk\'s side.", "他在僧侣的旁边坐了下来。");
	text = text.replace("He stares out across the land, but there is hardly a shimmer of life in his eyes, though you certainly see the blood of his life leaving his backside as he treats himself to a beating.", "他凝视着大地，但他的眼睛里几乎没有一丝生命的微光，尽管你肯定能看到他在殴打自己时，生命的血液从他的背部流出。");
	text = text.replace("You step away once more, but the grass beneath your feet doesn\'t have the same crunch to it and the air carries a copper scent.", "你又一次离开，但脚下的草地却没有了那种嘎吱嘎吱的声音，空气中弥漫着一股金属的味道。");
	text = text.replace("NLittle leather snickers follow you all the way back to your tentice.", "带着一阵轻松的窃笑，你一路返回了你的帐篷。");

//flagellants_wounds_heal_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) the flagellant is found sitting cross-legged before a campfire\./, "$1 这个苦修者被发现盘腿坐在篝火前。");
	text = text.replace("He\'s all alone save the millmoths fluttering dangerously close to the flames.", "只有他一个人，尝试拯救着那些危险地扑向火焰的飞蛾。");
	text = text.replace("Sensing your presence, he calls you over.", "他感觉到你的存在，就叫你过去。");
	text = text.replace("You take a seat beside him and he smiles at you.", "你坐在他旁边，他对你微笑。");
	text = text.replace("I\'ve become a better man since joining this company.", "自从加入你的战队，我已经变成一个更好的人。");
	text = text.replace("You nod as he surely has. He continues.", "你点头，他当然也点头了。他继续道。");
	text = text.replace("I\'ve bled for the gods a great deal, but my wounds... they are but scars now.", "我为神流了很多血，但我的伤口…现在它们只是伤疤。");
	text = text.replace("I feel stronger than ever.", "我感觉比以前更强壮了。");
	text = text.replace("Again you nod, but then quickly ask if he is going to stop hurting himself.", "你再次点头，但很快问他是否会停止伤害自己。");
	text = text.replace("The man\'s eyes stare into the red-brimming embers.", "这个男人的眼睛凝视着烧红的灰烬。");
	text = text.replace("He shakes his head no.", "他摇摇头不。");
	text = text.replace("I will bleed for the gods until they say no more.", "我会为神明们流血，直到他们不再说话。");
	text = text.replace("Wondering aloud, you ask if the gods have spoken to him at all.", "你大声地疑惑着，问神明们是否对他说过话。");
	text = text.replace("Without a pause the man shakes his head no again.", "那人不假思索，又摇了摇头。");
	text = text.replace("They have not and so I shall bleed until their silence is broken or until I join them in the forever quiet.", "他们还没有开口，所以我要流血，直到他们的沉默被打破，或者直到我在永远的宁静中加入他们。");

//flagellation_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) approaches with a pained look on his face\./, "$1 带着痛苦的表情走过来。");
	text = text.replace("His helmet is in hand as he wipes his brow.", "他手里拿着头盔，另一只手擦着额头。");
	text = text.replace("Sir, uh, you should come and see this.", "先生，呃，你应该过来看看这个。");
	text = text.replace("You inquire as to what it is you are going to see.", "你打听你要去看什么。");
	text = text.replace("I don\'t have the words for it.", "我没有合适的词来形容它。");
	text = text.replace("You\'d best come and see with your own eyes.", "你最好亲眼来看看。");
	text = text.replace("You look down at your work - plotting the march for the coming days - but, judging by the look on the brother\'s face, it can wait.", "你低头看着你的工作－计划着未来几天的行程－但是，从这个队员脸上的表情来判断，这事可以缓一缓。");
	
	text = text.replace("You get up and have him lead you to whatever it is that\'s causing an issue.", "你站起来，让他把你引到出现问题的地方。");
	text = text.replace("You come across a throng of brothers circled around something or someone.", "你遇到一群队员围着某物或某人转。");
	text = text.replace(/Breaking your way through the crowd, the company quiets as you come into the clearing to find (.*?) the flagellant unconscious on the ground\./, "你冲破人群，当你进入空地时，战队安静了下来，因为你发现 $1 这个苦修者昏迷不醒地躺在地上。");
	text = text.replace("His back is stripped raw and you think you can even see a rib or two.", "他的背部被抽得很烂，你甚至可以看到一两根肋骨。");
	text = text.replace("Thorns have broken off his brutish whip, embedding themselves in his flesh, and his skin hangs in strands where it hangs at all.", "皮鞭上的荆棘折断了，扎进它的肉里，他的皮也随着骨骼而下垂。");
	text = text.replace("It is good he has passed out.", "幸好他已经昏倒了。");
	text = text.replace("Not because he would be horrible in pain, but because you think he might not otherwise have stopped.", "不是因为他会很痛苦，而是因为你觉得他可能不会停下来。");
	text = text.replace("You order the men to clean him up, dress his wounds, and hide his tools of misery.", "你命令队员们把他弄干净，给他包扎伤口，把他的自虐工具藏起来。");

//flagellation_horrifies_other_event.nut
	text = text.replace("Flesh torn asunder. Parts of man rendered unfamiliar.", "皮开肉绽。人类身体的某些部分显得很难理解。");
	text = text.replace("A copper stench in the air.", "空气中弥漫着血腥味。");
	text = text.replace("These are the things you find when beckoned by a brother\'s call.", "当你的兄弟召唤你时，你发现这些事情。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) the flagellant stooped over on a stump, his whole body unmoving save for his arm which flicks a glass and thorn-peppered whip against his own back\./, "$1 这个苦修者俯身在一根树桩上，全身一动不动，只剩下一只胳膊拿着酒杯和带刺的鞭子抽打自己的背。");
	text = text.replace(/A gargling belch draws your eyes to (.*?) who is bent over in the tall grass losing his lunch\./, "一个含着口水的打嗝声把你的眼睛吸引到 $1 身上，他正在高高的草丛中弯腰，把午餐吐出来了。");
	text = text.replace(/Sensing that he is disturbing the others, (.*?) cracks something of a smile that doesn\'t falter an inch to the horror he\'s committing to his own hide\./, "当意识到他在打扰别人时，$1 露出一丝微笑，笑得一点也不像他自己隐藏的那样恐怖。");
	text = text.replace(/Fear not the reaper, (.*?), I shall bleed even more in favor of saving your soul\./, "恐惧不是死神，$1，我将流更多的血来拯救你的灵魂。");

//food_goes_bad_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/While pulling inventory duty, (.*?) alerts you to a bit of dire news: a good sum of food has gone bad\./, "在清点存货的时候，$1 提醒你一个可怕的消息：一大堆食物坏了。");
	text = text.replace("Simple and to the point, you nod and thank him for telling you quickly.", "简洁而中肯，你点头并感谢他这么快告诉你。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) comes to you rubbing his jaw\./, "$1 来到你面前擦他的下巴。");
	text = text.replace("He says he almost broke his teeth on a bit of bread.", "他说他几乎被一小块面包硌碎了牙齿。");
	text = text.replace("Apparently he found the piece at the bottom of a food crate and it appears to have been sitting there for some time.", "显然，他是在一个食品箱的底部发现了这片东西，而且它似乎已经在那里放了一段时间了。");
	text = text.replace("You take a sword to the loaf, chopping it in two as a few brothers cheer with sarcastic bravado.", "你拿起一把剑，把面包劈成两半，几个兄弟用具有讽刺意味的虚张声势来庆祝。");
	text = text.replace("Taking up the halved bread, you show the men the insides: a dark core of black.", "拿起切成两半的面包，给他们看里面：一团漆黑。");
	text = text.replace("That\'s what your stomach will look like if you eat this, you say before throwing the bread into the bushes where you can hear it tumbling like a heavy stone.", "如果你吃了这个，你的胃就会是这个样子，你会咆哮，然后把面包扔进灌木丛，在那里你可以听到它像一块沉重的石头一样翻滚。");
	
	text = text.replace(/While pulling inventory duty, (.*?) alerts you to a bit of dire news: a good sum of food has gone bad\./, "在清点存货的时候，$1 提醒你一个可怕的消息：一大堆食物坏了。");
	text = text.replace("Simple and to the point, you nod and thank him for telling you quickly.", "简洁而中肯，你点头并感谢他这么快告诉你。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) yelps and leaps up off the log he was sitting on\./, "$1 坐在木头上，突然大叫一声，跳了起来。");
	text = text.replace("You walk over to see he\'s thrown a fish by the wayside and he can\'t stop pointing at it.", "你走过去看他把一条鱼扔在路边，他不停地指着它。");
	text = text.replace("While he warns you to not go near it, you decide to go near it.", "当他警告你不要靠近它时，你决定靠近它。");
	text = text.replace("Apparently a water-spider had birthed a clutch of eggs inside the fish\'s abdomen.", "很明显，一只水蜘蛛在鱼的腹部产了一窝卵。");
	text = text.replace("You now stare at the little spiderlings bubbling forth in a cloud of scuttling legs and bodies.", "你现在盯着那些小蜘蛛，它们的腿和身体像一团烟雾一样冒出来。");
	text = text.replace("Throwing the entire lot into a fire, you ask the brother to check the rest of the fish.", "把所有的鱼都扔进火里，你让那个队员检查剩下的鱼。");
	text = text.replace("Unfortunately, they are all in a similar state and nobody is willing to replace fish-food for spider-food.", "不幸的是，它们都处于相似的状态，没有人愿意用蜘蛛肉替代鱼肉。");
	
	text = text.replace(/While pulling inventory duty, (.*?) alerts you to a bit of dire news: a good sum of food has gone bad\./, "在清点存货的时候，$1 提醒你一个可怕的消息：一大堆食物坏了。");
	text = text.replace("Simple and to the point, you nod and thank him for telling you quickly.", "简洁而中肯，你点头并感谢他这么快告诉你。");
	text = text.replace(/You sift through a few crates of foodstuffs to find an entire carton of apples covered in what looks like grey fur\. (.*?) has a word for it, but you\'ve never heard it before\./, "你在几箱食品中仔细挑选，结果发现一整箱的苹果都覆盖着一层灰色的毛状物。$1 对此说了一个词，但你以前从未听说过它。");
	text = text.replace("Regardless, none of it can be salvaged and you toss the rotten fruit away.", "不管怎样，这些水果都无法挽救，你只能把腐烂的水果扔掉。");
	
	text = text.replace(/While pulling inventory duty, (.*?) alerts you to a bit of dire news: a good sum of food has gone bad\./, "在清点存货的时候，$1 提醒你一个可怕的消息：一大堆食物坏了。");
	text = text.replace("Simple and to the point, you nod and thank him for telling you quickly.", "简洁而中肯，你点头并感谢他这么快告诉你。");
	text = text.replace("Maggots wriggle about a few chunks of meat.", "蛆在几块肉上蠕动。");
	text = text.replace("Your men stare at the food, some looking as though they\'re willing to risk a bit of illness to have a bite.", "你的人盯着食物看，有些人看起来好像愿意冒着生病的风险来咬一口。");
	text = text.replace("You tell everyone off and get rid of the meat personally before someone does something stupid.", "在有人做出蠢事之前，你会告诫每个人，并亲自把肉处理掉。");
	
	text = text.replace("Childish giggling wakes you from a nap.", "幼稚的傻笑把你从午睡中吵醒。");
	text = text.replace("You rise up to see that some of the food is gone and the only evidence as to where it departed is a field of still moving tall grass.", "你站起来，发现一些食物不见了，唯一能证明食物去向的地方是一片仍在移动的高草。");
	text = text.replace("Thinking fast, you take up a sword and follow its trail.", "不假思索，你拿起一把剑，跟随它的踪迹。");
	text = text.replace("Unfortunately, it isn\'t long before you are lost in the midst of enormous stalks of green that pedal against your face with every rush of wind.", "不幸的是，没过多久，你迷失在巨大的绿色植物中，每一阵风吹过，这些植物就会盖在你的脸上。");
	text = text.replace("The giggling doesn\'t stop, however, and you hear the pitter-patter of footsteps cross behind you and then in front.", "然而，咯咯的笑声并没有停止，你听到了身后和前面传来的脚步声。");
	text = text.replace("A voice speaks, sounding like a child deep in a well.", "一个声音在说话，听起来就像一个孩子在深井里。");
	text = text.replace("Chase us! Over here! Chase us! Chase us... CHASE US. CHASE US NOW!", "追我们啊！在这里！追我们！追我们…追我们。赶紧追我们！");
	text = text.replace("You suddenly feel no urge to retrieve the grain.", "你突然觉得没有想要取回粮食的冲动。");
	text = text.replace("You slowly put your sword back in its sheath and back out of the field.", "你慢慢地把你的剑放回剑鞘，然后退出这个地方。");
	text = text.replace("As you stare into the tall grass, it begins to part, slowly, like a piece of leather being torn at the seams.", "当你凝视着高高的草丛时，它开始慢慢地分开，就像一块被撕破的皮革。");
	text = text.replace("You hear horrible cries as each stem cracks in half.", "你听到可怕的哭泣声，就像每个植物的茎裂成两半。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) startles you when he asks what it is you\'re doing\./, "$1 问你在做什么时，他吓了你一跳。");
	text = text.replace("You turn to look at him, then turn back to the field which sways gently to a breeze.", "你转过头去看他，然后又转回那随风轻轻摇摆的田野。");
	text = text.replace("Instead of answering, you just tell him to get ready as you\'ll be marching again very soon.", "你没有回答，只是告诉他准备好，因为你很快就会再次出发。");
	text = text.replace("Thankfully, the mercenary does not inquire about the missing food.", "值得庆幸的是，雇佣兵们并没有询问丢失的食物。");

//forestlover_event .nut
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) looks up at the forest canopy, his hand playfully strumming through the lightfalls\./, "$1 抬头看向林中树冠，手嬉戏般的在泻下的阳光中撩拨。");
	text = text.replace("He looks at you.", "他看着你。");
	text = text.replace("I used to play through these forests as a kid.", "我小时候常在这些森林中玩耍。");
	text = text.replace("You nod, then wonder aloud.", "你表示赞同，接着大声发出质疑。");
	text = text.replace(/I thought you were born outside (.*?)\?/, "我以为你的出生地附近是 $1 ？");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?)\'s hand falls and he stares at the ground\./, "$1 放下他的手，注视着地面。");
	text = text.replace("Oh yeah, that\'s right.", "噢，是的，你说对了。");
	text = text.replace("Well, we should get moving then, right?", "好了，我们该动身了对吧？");
	text = text.replace("Before you can say anything more, the red-faced man marches on.", "在你能说点什么出来之前，这个人脸红着走了。");
	text = text.replace(/You find that (.*?) appears to be in better spirits lately\./, "你发现 $1 似乎最近心情变好了。");
	text = text.replace("As it turns out, these forests are familiar to him and a return to their greenery has the man beaming with warm nostalgia.", "原来，他很熟悉森林，重返绿荫让他散发出一种温暖的怀乡气氛。");
	text = text.replace("Even though you\'ve marched through plenty of forests, this one\'s viridscapes has you impressed.", "即使你曾踏足过不少森林，这样的青翠景致仍使你印象深刻。");
	text = text.replace(/No doubt (.*?) is loving a return to the trees\' thick domain\./, "毫无疑问 $1 爱极了重返浓郁的绿荫。");
	text = text.replace(/Trees, fat trunks and strong-limbed, rise above you\. (.*?) seems to be mesmerized by their towering\./, "树木粗壮的的枝干在你头顶延伸开来。$1 似乎沉浸于它们的环绕中。");
	text = text.replace("You find the man smiling all the time lately, as though a return to the forest is a return to better times.", "你发现他最近一直在笑，好似重返森林也重返了那些美好的日子。");

//gambler_vs_other_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) and (.*?) walk up to mottled with bruises\./, "$1 和 $2 浑身是伤地走过来。");
	text = text.replace("It appears they\'ve been in a bit of a scuffle.", "看起来他们打了一架。");
	text = text.replace("Seeing as how neither one is dead, you don\'t really care what it was over, but they tell you anyway.", "不过既然俩人都还好好地喘着气儿，你并不想知道出了什么事，但他们还是告诉你了。");
	text = text.replace("Apparently the gambler took some money in a bit of sly cardsmanship.", "很显然，这个赌徒为了赢钱耍了些不那么光明正大的小伎俩。");
	text = text.replace("You ask either man if the company\'s money was involved. They say no.", "你问他们这事儿有没有涉及到战队的资金。他们说没有。");
	text = text.replace("You ask what the hell they want from you then.", "你问他们还来找你干嘛。");
	text = text.replace(/A game of cards comes to a table-flipping end when (.*?) jumps off his stool and launches a tirade at (.*?)\. The professional gambler looks around with sheepish incredulity\./, "一场牌局竟是如此收场，$1 从凳子上跳起来掀了桌子，指着 $2 一通大骂。这个以前的职业赌棍却顾左右而言它。");
	text = text.replace("How could such a man come into so much money over a game of cards, he asks, but when his hands go up to feign confusion a few \'extra\' cards slip out of his sleeves.", "这怎么可能，谁能一下赢走那么多钱，但是当他的手举起来假装困惑时，几张“多余的”纸牌却从他袖子里溜了出来。");
	text = text.replace("The ensuing battle is amusing, but you put a stop to it before anyone gets hurt.", "接下来的那场打斗无疑极具观赏性，不过你在有人伤得太重之前把他们拉开了。");

//giant_tree_in_forest_event.nut
	text = text.replace("You pass through a wall of shrubs and find yourself stopped by quite a sight.", "你穿过一道茂密的灌木丛，被眼前的景象所震惊。");
	text = text.replace("To call it a tree would seem insulting.", "若是把眼前的这个东西仅仅叫做一棵树或许对它是一种冒犯。");
	text = text.replace("The trees about it are so low beneath their neighbor they appear to be bending at midtrunk, swearing fealty to that which is arboreally suzerain, a domain rippled with roots as thick as any man, and enough shade above to lose time between the days and night.", "这周围的林木都朝着中心弯下腰，似是在向这树中的宗主表示敬意，那巨木粗壮的根系暴露在地面上，每一根分叉都足有你的腰那么粗，其头顶绿茵遮天蔽日，你甚至无法分清这是白天还是夜晚。");
	text = text.replace(/You walk to the base of the enormity and run a hand along its bark, but then you stop, fearing that your flesh may have just trespassed upon holy ground like a child tumbling playfully into a church of one wholly quiet crowd\. (.*?) the monk comes to your side nodding and with his hands firmly behind his back\./, "你走到树干旁边，用手掌轻轻抚过树皮，但又立刻停下来，因为你意识到此时的行为或许与无知顽童闯进肃穆教堂一般无异。僧侣 $1 背着手慢悠悠地走过来。");
	text = text.replace("This is a godtree.", "这是一棵有灵的神树。");
	text = text.replace("The roots go through the earth and into the realm of the gods.", "其根系洞穿我们脚下的厚土，联通神灵的领域。");
	text = text.replace("It is said they once listened, but now... we are not so sure.", "据说神灵也曾侧耳聆听尘世众生，不过现在…现在的事谁又说得清楚呢。");
	text = text.replace("You stare at the man, and his particularly withheld posture, and ask if he fears the tree.", "你盯着这个人，他的站姿格外矜持，于是你问他对这棵树是否畏惧。");
	text = text.replace("He smiles at you and shakes his head.", "他微笑着摇摇头。");
	text = text.replace("I respect it like a man would the sea, for the waters of the oceans hold many things to fear and, yet, the sailor sails anyway.", "我对它怀有敬意，就像一个人面对着汪洋大海，那阴郁深沉的洋面下掩藏着不知多少值得畏惧的东西，但水手无论如何都还在航行。");
	text = text.replace("Were the ocean a docile beast, would man refer to it so lovingly?", "要是连大海都变得温顺驯良，人们又何必对它怀有敬畏之心呢？");

//glutton_gets_fat_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/You find (.*?) helping himself to a third helping of food\./, "你看见 $1 已经第三次在找食了。");
	text = text.replace("That\'s far too much and so you demand that it be his last.", "他吃的太多了，于是你勒令这是他今天最后一次吃东西。");
	text = text.replace("Another brother joins in, mocking the man for his habits.", "一位兄弟凑过来，嘲笑他的食量。");
	text = text.replace("The glutton, enraged, slams his food down and stands up.", "馋嘴的家伙勃然大怒，一把摔下手中的吃食站了起来。");
	text = text.replace("His stomach however, sways at a different pace than the rest of him and the rather fattened man goes down in a heap of flailing limbs.", "但他的肚子却没那么听话，软软的甩起来使他失去了重心一屁股坐倒在地，摔成一滩挥舞着手臂的肉山。");
	text = text.replace("While the rest of the company has a laugh, you can\'t help but wonder if the sellsword really has gotten too fat.", "就在其他兄弟们大笑不止的时候，你不得不担心这个佣兵是不是太胖了。");

//goblin_land_event.nut
	text = text.replace("You find a dead goblin.", "你看见一只死去的哥布林。");
	text = text.replace("But it\'s no ordinary goblin - this is an elder.", "这不是一般的哥布林－而是一只哥布林长老。");
	text = text.replace("He or she\'s showing signs of dying of old age.", "它浑身上下都透着一股衰老的迹象。");
	text = text.replace("There\'s also ceremonial trinkets all about it.", "随身还有不少古怪的首饰。");
	text = text.replace("This here goblin didn\'t get here by accident: it died and received a proper burial.", "这样一头哥布林可不会随便死在荒郊野外：它是被妥善下葬的。");
	text = text.replace("Which means only one thing: you\'re in those damned greenskins\' territory.", "这意味着一件事：你正在这些该死的绿皮的地盘上。");
	text = text.replace("You come across a dead dog on a hillside.", "你在山坡下边看见一条死去的狗。");
	text = text.replace("Its tongue hangs out, its eyes almost ready to pop from the skull.", "舌头耷拉在嘴边，眼睛因为腐烂的尸气而鼓胀欲出。");
	text = text.replace(/A number of darts are sticking out of its fur\. (.*?) plucks one and looks at the tallowed tips of metal\./, "几根箭插在它的毛皮下边。$1 把它拔出来仔细检查这锋锐的金属刺。");
	text = text.replace("Goblin poison.", "哥布林毒药。");
	text = text.replace("You inquire as to why the dog, though. The man shrugs.", "你问为什么会用在一条狗身上。那人耸耸肩。");
	text = text.replace("A scared dog makes for good target practice, I suppose.", "用受惊的狗当箭靶，可能吧。");
	text = text.replace("A wreath of odd and discolored flowers, weeds, and tree limbs.", "你看见一丛颜色异常艳丽的野花、杂草和灌木。");
	text = text.replace("Amongst them, dozens of large beetles rattle as their shells bump into one another.", "在那上边，几十只硕大的甲虫正疯狂的厮斗，闪着诡异光泽的甲壳迸发出冲撞声。");
	text = text.replace(/They seem to be feasting on the sap or other oddity seeping from the vegetative collection\. (.*?) wonders aloud\./, "看起来它们正在争相抢夺这堆植物里渗出的汁液或是别的什么东西。$1 突然张口说。");
	text = text.replace("I think I\'ve seen one of these before.", "我好像在哪见过这样的东西。");
	text = text.replace("It\'s some sort of marking.", "像是某种标记。");
	text = text.replace("You glance at him.", "你瞥了他一眼。");
	text = text.replace("We need to be keeping an eye out for bored spinsters or something?", "怎么，这地方有人看场子吗？");
	//text = text.replace("The man shakes his head.", "那人摇了摇头。");
	text = text.replace("Naw. This here is a goblin\'s fabrication.", "不。这是哥布林放在这儿的。");
	text = text.replace("We\'re in their land now.", "我们现在在它们的领地上了。");
	text = text.replace("While marching through the land, you come across a dead orc.", "你们正在大路上行军，突然看见一只死去的兽人。");
	text = text.replace("He seems almost unhurt, as though you\'d stumbled across him sleeping.", "他好像没受什么伤，乍一看简直就像是睡着了一样。");
	text = text.replace("But when you get a closer look, you spot almost a dozen small darts sticking out of his side.", "但凑近一看，这兽人背上和腋下还插着十几只纤细的小箭。");
	text = text.replace("You immediately get a good look at your surroundings, then turn to your men.", "你俯下身子四下打量，然后转向你的手下。");
	text = text.replace("Step carefully, men, we\'re in goblin territory now.", "要小心了，我们现在在哥布林的领土上。");
	text = text.replace("You find a number stones arranged into a circle.", "你看见几块石头被排列成一个圆环。");
	text = text.replace("In the middle of this oddity is a human skull with its top cut away.", "中间摆着一个人的头骨，头盖骨已然不翼而飞。");
	text = text.replace("Inside the brainpan are a number of what appear to be dice and chicken bones.", "颅腔里边盛着一些像是骰子或鸡骨头的小玩意儿。");
	text = text.replace("Such shamanistic designs aren\'t found by accident - you\'re in goblin lands.", "这样充满原始宗教气息的装饰绝非偶然－你现在一定是在哥布林的领地里了。");
	text = text.replace("You come across a dead deer ensnared by a horrifying trap.", "在一个可怕的陷阱里边，你看见一条死去的鹿。");
	text = text.replace("It would have all the markings of an ordinary trap - one that intends to kill via spikes - were it not for the obvious poison tips it came laden with.", "乍一眼看上去跟那些尖刺陷坑一般无二，只是那些削尖的木桩上很明显上了毒。");
	text = text.replace("Poison that is unique to one group only: goblins.", "而只有一种东西会用这样的毒药：哥布林。");
	text = text.replace("Best step carefully from now on.", "接下来的路得小心些了。");
	text = text.replace("A smoldering fire. Sticks and stones arranged for this or that.", "一堆焖烧的灰烬。周围几块焦黑的石头和木棍。");
	text = text.replace("One standing armory stocked with blowguns.", "琳琅满目的兵器散落一地。");
	text = text.replace("Curved blades. And one dead wolf pup with a leash around its neck.", "弯刃刀。还有一条死去的幼狼，脖子上挂着嚼头。");
	text = text.replace("Having observed this evidence, you quickly inform the men of what circumstances are before them.", "看见这一幕，你赶紧告诉手下们。");
	text = text.replace("This is goblin territory, men, and by the look of things they aren\'t far, either.", "我们在哥布林的领地，而且看起来它们不久前才离开。");
	text = text.replace("A litter of dead wolf pups.", "地上散落着几只死去的小狼崽。");
	text = text.replace("Their open-bellied mother is by them, a collar around her neck.", "它们的母亲被开膛破肚，扔在一边，脖子上还戴着项圈。");
	text = text.replace("There\'s a line of gore trailing away from the scene, some tiny footsteps in the grass.", "一条血迹斑斑的足迹引向深草丛里。");
	text = text.replace("The goblins been gettin\' more of their mounts.", "这是哥布林在抓捕它们的骑兽呢。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) is by your side\./, "$1 站在你身边。");
	text = text.replace("He points at the pups.", "他指着那些小崽。");
	text = text.replace("They say the gobbos like the wild ones.", "听说哥布林最喜欢那些野生的。");
	text = text.replace("They look for the freshest litters and only take the strongest.", "一胎之中只挑选那些最强壮的。");
	text = text.replace("All you\'re hearing is that you are in goblin territory.", "你明白自己这是在哥布林的领地里了。");
	text = text.replace("You advise the men to keep a close eye on their surroundings, lest the tricky gits get the drop on you.", "你叫手下们盯紧周围，别让那些狡猾的东西偷袭了我们。");

//good_food_variety_event.nut
	text = text.replace("You watch as the men chow down on plates about as colorful as the men\'s personalities.", "餐盘里的食物就像人们的性格那样丰富多彩。");
	text = text.replace("Supplying the company with such a diverse stock of food has raised their spirits as good as any victory!", "能够让大家吃上如此丰富的食物无疑会大大提振士气！");
	text = text.replace("A hot meal is what any man needs, but a hot meal, with a couple of sides and entrees?", "人人都得吃上一顿热腾腾的饱饭，若不仅是一餐热饭，再加上几件配菜和点心？");
	text = text.replace("Well, that\'s something else entirely!", "那可就太棒了！");
	text = text.replace("Your purchases of diverse foods has the men gleefully chowing down and feeling good about life.", "你所提供的丰富多样的食物让人们大饱口福之余还提振了士气。");
	text = text.replace("Food as diverse as any nobleman\'s - or close enough, anyway.", "你们的伙食比得上贵族盛宴－或者至少差不多吧。");
	text = text.replace("That\'s what you have supplied the company and the men are supremely appreciative as they chow down.", "你能以如此丰盛的美食喂饱战队，使得大家在大饱口福之余对你心怀感激。");

//graverobber_finds_item_event.nut
	text = text.replace("The weather is nice.", "天气不错。");
	text = text.replace("A fine evening, if any, for the moon to be where it is: an orange rind of it slipping in and out of the clouds - clouds that pass by on the seemingly innocuous gesture that a light breeze can have.", "这是一个美好的夜晚，一丝丝暖橘色的月光透出云层－云彩摆动着优雅的肢体，被清风吹散。");
	text = text.replace("So bright is this rim of a moon you wonder if any flowers might bloom, mistaking the evening light for its brighter cousin.", "月轮一下变得如此明亮，你在想，会不会有花蕾看见了这月光，以为天光大亮而尽情开放。");
	text = text.replace("You wonder if the millmoths and flies and armor-backed beetles see the moon and dance toward it as they would any candle or torch.", "你在想，蚊蝇、飞蛾和甲壳虫，会不会绕着月亮跳舞，就像它们对跳动的烛火那样。");
	text = text.replace("Do they have that quiet desperation?", "他们也能意识到么？");
	text = text.replace("That inescapable cruelty of realizing that, when your stock is placed against the greater whole, you have and are nothing... and the hatred that realization can bring, and the jealousy...", "面对这庞大的宇宙星河，你和你的部队不过是渺小的沧海一粟，这是多么残酷而无法逃离的明悟…面对这现实，你怎么能不愤恨，不嫉妒…");
	text = text.replace(/Suddenly, (.*?) the graverobber appears by your side, his smell skewering your thoughts with miasmic proficiency\./, "突然，盗墓贼 $1 走到你旁边，身上刺鼻的气味一下把你的思绪吹散了。");
	text = text.replace("He\'s hardly a man at all, but a golem, mudslaked and grass-peppered with two white eyes peering out.", "你几乎认不出这是个人了，他看起来就像一座泥石搭建的傀儡，浑身覆盖着一层泥水和散碎草叶，只有两只白白的眼睛依稀可辨。");
	text = text.replace("Sighing, you ask what he wants.", "你叹气，问他想干啥。");
	text = text.replace("He thumbs over one shoulder, the other occupied by a shovel.", "他用大拇指指指背后，其他人都拄着铁锹。");
	text = text.replace("Went digging through a grave or three.", "我们去开了几个墓。");
	text = text.replace("Found somethin\' and I don\'t mean just what them graves are for.", "看到了些有意思的东西，当然不只是坟墓本埋的东西。");
	text = text.replace("Wanna come take a look?", "要来看看吗？");
	text = text.replace("Of course you do...", "那当然了…");
	
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) brings you to a big hole in the ground\./, "$1 把你带到一个大坑边上。");
	text = text.replace("The top half of a skeleton is at the bottom, its arms loose over the earth as though it had bedded there for a night\'s rest.", "坑底露出半具骨架，手臂撑在地上，就好像是在打瞌睡。");
	text = text.replace("Empty eye sockets look up at you.", "空洞的眼眶却直勾勾地盯着你。");
	text = text.replace("The graverobber crouches and grabs something.", "盗墓贼弯腰捡起什么东西。");
	text = text.replace("He wipes the mud and worms off it and hands it over.", "甩掉上面的泥土又用衣服擦干净递给你。");
	text = text.replace("I think we can use that.", "这东西我们能用得上。");
	text = text.replace("You nod, but tell the man to quickly fill the grave before anyone sees what he\'s done.", "你点头，叫他在被人发现之前快把墓填了。");
	
	text = text.replace(/While looking down at the goods, (.*?) the rather astute scholar and historian sidles up next to you\./, "当你低头检视这些东西时，$1 这位相当精明的学者兼历史学家侧身坐在你旁边。");
	text = text.replace("He\'s rubbing his chin and a faint hum ruminates deeply within him.", "他一边抓耳挠腮，口中喃喃自语。");
	text = text.replace("Yes, yes...", "是的，没错…");
	text = text.replace("You turn to him to ask what he\'s going on about.", "你问他什么意思。");
	text = text.replace("He snaps his fingers and points down at what the graverobber had found.", "他打了个响指，指着盗墓贼找到的东西。");
	text = text.replace(/He explains that this isn\'t just any chest plate or weapon, but indeed the gear of a famous fighter, nobleman, and womanizer, (.*?)\./, "他说这些东西不是一般的家伙，而是属于一位著名的斗士、贵族和情圣，$1。");

//graverobber_heist_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) the grimy graverobber enters your tent with his hands behind his back\./, "$1 那个阴暗的盗墓贼，把手藏在背后的阴影里走进你的帐篷。");
	text = text.replace("You don\'t wish to delay what madness has been brought before you much longer, so you go ahead and ask what the man wants.", "你不想看他再故弄玄虚，于是直接问他想干啥。");
	text = text.replace("Sir... I\'ve...", "先生…我听说…");
	text = text.replace("I\'ve gotten word that a local baron - a wealthy man, indeed! - has been recently put to rest in a graveyard not far from here.", "我听说本地一位男爵－一个有钱的男爵！－最近下葬了，就埋在离这儿不远的地方。");
	text = text.replace("Leaning back in your chair, you give the man a shrug. He continues.", "你换了个舒服的坐姿，耸耸肩。他接着说。");
	text = text.replace("I don\'t wish to ask the other men to help, for they look at me like some sort of horrid thing.", "我不敢叫上别人，他们看我的眼神叫我不舒服。");
	text = text.replace("I... . But you... you\'re different.", "我…。但是你…你不一样。");
	text = text.replace("You hired me after all.", "无论如何是你把我雇来的。");
	text = text.replace("You lean forward, drawing your armor taught and the chair beneath you to a groaning wooden whine.", "你向前凑了凑，身上的铠甲压得屁股下面的椅子发出一声扭曲的短促哀嚎。");
	text = text.replace("Let me guess: you want me to help you dig up this baron\'s grave.", "让我想想：你想叫我跟你去挖了那个男爵的坟。");
	text = text.replace("The man grins, a pathetic sight, one that reminds you of the time you scolded a dog for stealing a biscuit.", "那人咧嘴一笑，一副可怜的样子，让你想起那次你骂狗偷饼干。");
	
	text = text.replace("Having excused yourself from the excavating expedition, you get back to work.", "你说服自己不要参加这场挖掘计划，接着做手上的活计。");
	text = text.replace("Time flies, millmoths arcing in rote loops about a candle that droops lower and lower, its glassy flame so easily flicked to the wingbeats of the creatures about it.", "时间悄悄走过，飞蛾绕着烛火飞舞，透明的火焰不时灼烧着这小东西的翅膀。");
	text = text.replace(/Finally, (.*?) returns, heaving a bit of a chest into the tent\./, "终于，$1 回来了，怀里抱着一个箱子走进帐篷。");
	text = text.replace("He looks more mud than man.", "他满身都是泥。");
	text = text.replace("I got it, sir!", "我弄到了，先生！");
	text = text.replace("The graverobber quickly looks behind himself, then says again, his voice a bit quieter this time.", "盗墓贼神经兮兮地回头看了一眼，又开口了，这次他的声音低了一点。");
	text = text.replace("I got it... I got all of it.", "我弄到了…我把东西全弄来了。");
	text = text.replace("Look, I\'ll split it with you.", "这样，我会分你一点。");
	text = text.replace("I mean, you didn\'t help me avoid the watchman, or shovel up the earth, or drag the body out, or drag the chest out, or put the coffin back in its place, or put the dirt back on the coffin, or avoid the watchman a second time, or drag the chest all the way into camp... but you did let me do it!", "我是说，虽然你没有帮我躲过巡逻队，没有帮我挖土，也没帮我把尸体拽出来，帮我抬出箱子，帮我把棺材放回去，帮我填土，帮我再一次躲过巡逻队，再把这箱子一路拖回营地…不过你好歹让我去了！");
	
	text = text.replace("Having excused yourself from the excavating expedition, you get back to work.", "你说服自己不要参加这场挖掘计划，接着做手上的活计。");
	text = text.replace("Time flies, millmoths arcing in rote loops about a candle that droops lower and lower, its glassy flame so easily flicked to the wingbeats of the creatures about it.", "时间悄悄走过，飞蛾绕着烛火飞舞，透明的火焰不时灼烧着这小东西的翅膀。");
	text = text.replace(/Finally, (.*?) returns, the first sign of him the edge of your tent flap moving just so\./, "终于，$1 回来了，他从帐篷门口露出半个脑袋。");
	text = text.replace("You set your quillpen down and ask the man to enter.", "你放下羽毛笔，叫他进来。");
	text = text.replace("He does so, rather tentatively, as a man about to cross a threshold he\'d rather not.", "他小心翼翼地挪进去，看得出来他完全不想进来。");
	text = text.replace("Even in the dim candlelight you can see the colors darkness is so ordinarily good at hiding: purples and blues and dark reds. He grins sheepishly.", "就着昏暗的烛光，你看见这个家伙的身上就像开了间染坊：青一块紫一块，有的地方还见了红。他不好意思地笑笑。");
	text = text.replace("They, uh, caught me sir.", "先生，他们，呃，他们抓住我了。");
	//text = text.replace("You nod.", "你点头。");
	text = text.replace("Yes, I can see that.", "嗯，我看出来了。");
	text = text.replace("The man quickly raises a finger, a slop of mud flying waywardly into nowhere but a wet sound.", "那人猛地举起一只手，不知从哪甩出一块污泥，飞进黑暗里发出一声闷响。");
	text = text.replace("But next time!", "不过下次！");
	text = text.replace("You stop the man with a raised hand.", "你赶紧伸手叫他闭嘴。");
	text = text.replace("How about you go get patched up and then we\'ll talk about this \'next time\', yeah?", "要不这样，你先去包扎一下，然后咱们再来聊聊你这个下次，嗯？");
	
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) is not the pillar upon which you wish to sacrifice your good standing in the world - or at least, what good standing a mercenary can have\./, "$1 不是你打算在这地方搞坏你的名声－虽然雇佣兵原本就没啥好名声。");
	text = text.replace(/You tell (.*?) that not only will you not be accompanying him, but that you refuse to let him go off and do this alone\./, "你告诉 $1 你不会帮他，而且他自己也不许去。");
	text = text.replace("He pouts like a young hunter whose bow has been taken away by an angry father.", "他失落极了，看着就像一个年轻的猎人被愤怒的父亲抢走了猎弓。");
	text = text.replace("Well... alright then...", "那…那好吧…");
	text = text.replace("I suppose it was only riches...", "只是几个钱而已…");
	
	text = text.replace(/You and (.*?) stalk low through the bushes, a gangly duo of absurdity, silhouettes murky and ruminating of obvious hijinks even in the darkest of nights\./, "你和 $1 矮着身子从灌木丛中爬过，即使是在这伸手不见五指的黑夜里，只要不是瞎子也能一眼认出你俩没怀着什么好心思。");
	text = text.replace("The two of you enter the graveyard as though you were to happen about it by accident, merrily pretending that what is to unfold next would surely not come from two stranges such as yourselves.", "你们若无其事地溜进墓地，装作无意间撞进去的样子，好像这样别人就不会怀疑一会要被挖开的坟墓是你们这两个外地佬干的似的。");
	text = text.replace("About the graveyard are rows and rows of gray slabs and marbled statues with no faces and black iron gates that hee-hawed in the wind.", "坟地旁边是一排排灰石和看不清面目的大理石像做成的栅栏，黑色的大铁门在夜风中吱吱作响。");
	text = text.replace("Tall grass everywhere, fertilizer in abundance.", "到处是齐腰高的杂草，很明显，此地土壤肥沃无比。");
	text = text.replace("Flowers homegrown and others laid down from elsewhere, and some a bit of both.", "野花和人们带来的花束散落得到处都是，亦有杂交品种。");
	text = text.replace("Pursing his lips, the graverobber turns about.", "盗墓贼环视一周，狠狠地抿了抿嘴唇。");
	text = text.replace("He stabs his shovel into the ground and puts his fists to his hips.", "他把铲子的头踩进泥土里，一只手叉着腰。");
	text = text.replace("Goddammit.", "该死。");
	text = text.replace("Sensing something off, you ask what\'s wrong.", "听出他语气不对劲，你问他咋了。");
	text = text.replace("He spits and answers.", "他张口说道。");
	text = text.replace("I can\'t \'member if it is that grave, that one, or that one.", "我想不起来他埋在哪了，是这个还是那个，也有可能是那边那个。");
	text = text.replace("He points to three different sites: one is a modest little stone, bleached and balded to commemorate a death; another is gated with gothic spires; another is but a door to a mausoleum.", "随着他的示意，你看向三座坟墓：其中一个是一块低矮的石头墓碑，风吹日晒已经变得十分光滑；其二是一圈哥特式的围栏，坟墓就被围在中间；第三个则是一座地下陵墓，大门紧闭。");
	text = text.replace("The graverobber turns to you.", "盗墓贼看向你。");
	text = text.replace("We probably don\'t have much time here, which grave you think it be?", "咱们不能在这儿多待，你说挖哪个？");
	
	text = text.replace("With a swift crack of your spade, the gothic gate is broken open.", "你拿起铲子猛地一敲，栅栏门应声而破。");
	text = text.replace("The twang of metal on metal is sent grumbling between the gravestones and swaying tree branches seem to snicker at your rather loud trespass.", "金属撞击的声音顿时回荡在墓碑之间，就连树枝都颤动着，好像在叫你小声点。");
	text = text.replace("When you swing the gate open, the hinges squall as if they themselves were awakened spirits.", "你猛地打开栅栏门，铰链吱吱作响，好像两只被惊醒的幽灵。");
	text = text.replace("You enter the little square plot and lean against the spires of the fence.", "你钻进围栏中间，扶着铁栏杆向外瞧。");
	text = text.replace(/A short order gets (.*?) to work while you keep a look out like a man unimpressed by the nature of his own crimes\./, "叫 $1 赶紧干活，你帮他把风。");
	text = text.replace("Some minutes of scrupulous shoveling later and the robber of graves is finished.", "经过几分钟小心翼翼的挖掘，你们完成了这次盗墓。");
	text = text.replace("What ends up being found is a very large coffin that has no hopes of being dragged out of the ground, not with just two men anyway.", "土里埋着的是一个硕大的棺材，一眼就看出凭你们两人的力气完全不可能把它抬出来。");
	text = text.replace("Using the same manner with which you dealt the gate a blow, you break the latches off the casket and throw it open.", "就像砸开铁门一样，你弄坏了棺材盖上的栓，把盖子掀开。");
	text = text.replace("A freshly-dead man stares back up at you, two stones painted with eyes rolling away from his sockets.", "一个刚死不久的人盯着你，用两只石头做的假眼睛。");
	text = text.replace("The sight startles you, but you quickly start rifling through the dead man\'s baggage.", "你吓了一跳，但很快就反应过来，伸手在他的行李里摸索。");
	text = text.replace(/As it turns out, (.*?) was right: the man was buried with great satchels of gold and goblets and golden goblets\./, "看来，$1 说的没错，这人身边有一大袋陪葬的金子、杯子和金子做的杯子。");
	text = text.replace("You take it all, close the casket, and sneak back out of the graveyard.", "你把它们全拿走了，关上棺材板，溜出墓园。");
	
	text = text.replace("You enter the mausoleum like a man fearful that the door behind him might forever snap closed.", "你走进陵墓，疑神疑鬼的，就好像背后的门随时会自己关上，把你们永远关在里面。");
	text = text.replace("The coffin rests on a slab of marble with candles burning about its four corners.", "棺椁被放置在一大块大理石地面上，四角摆着明亮的烛台。");
	text = text.replace("While there was no wind outside, you can\'t help but hear a faint moan of it circling about the room.", "空气中一丝风也没有，但你却隐约听见忽明忽灭的风声环绕着这间斗室。");
	text = text.replace(/Shaking away your fears, you and (.*?) push the casket\'s lid off, careful not to let it drop off the otherside and presumably wake half the town\./, "摇摇头把恐惧驱散，你和 $1 推开棺材板，小心地不让它摔到地上，那样发出的巨响恐怕会惊醒大半个镇子。");
	text = text.replace("Inside the sarcophagus, you find a man attired in a knight\'s clothing: a helmet, chest plate, and shield.", "在棺材里你看见一具穿着骑士装备的尸体：头盔，胸甲，身上盖着一面盾牌。");
	text = text.replace("His sword crosses his body from neck to groin, his hands clasped around the handle in a battle-ready embrace.", "一把宝剑从喉咙到胯下，双手握在剑柄之上。");
	text = text.replace(/You look to (.*?) who shrugs\./, "你看了 $1 一眼，后者耸肩。");
	text = text.replace("Suppose this fella was a knight.", "我猜这家伙生前是个骑士。");
	text = text.replace("You nod. The graverobber glances from dead man to living.", "你点头。盗墓贼从头到脚瞥了一下这位骑士。");
	text = text.replace("Suppose... this knight don\'t need that stuff no more...", "我猜…骑士大人用不上他生前的装备了…");
	text = text.replace("Seeing as how you don\'t plan to leave empty handed, you nod again.", "你不准备空手而归，于是同意了他的看法。");
	text = text.replace(/The dead knight puts up quite the fight as (.*?) struggles to free him of that which he no longer needs\./, "在 $1 扒下他的装备时，死掉的骑士奋力挣扎。");
	text = text.replace("After a few minutes of battle, you lend a hand in removing the helmet.", "经过几分钟的苦战，你帮着摘下了那顶头盔。");
	text = text.replace(/What falls out is a great bundle of blonde hair\. (.*?) steps back\./, "一大束金发一下子露出来。$1 向后退了一步。");
	text = text.replace("That\'s a woman!", "是个女人！");
	text = text.replace("Suddenly, voices rise up from outside the graveyard.", "突然，墓穴外传来说话声。");
	text = text.replace("You grab all the things you can and tell the graverobber to start running.", "你抱起地上的东西，告诉盗墓贼赶紧跑。");
	
	text = text.replace("Just as you take your shovel into hand, a man\'s voice calls out to you.", "你刚拿起铲子，突然有人朝你大吼。");
	text = text.replace("Just what in the hell do you think y\'all are doing?", "你们到底在干什么？");
	text = text.replace("You wheel around to see a man lighting a lantern.", "你回头一看，有个人提着灯走过来。");
	text = text.replace("He holds it up, the handle creaking as it swivels back and forth.", "他把提灯举起来，铁链左摇右摆嘎吱作响。");
	text = text.replace("Y\'all look like graverobbers to me.", "我猜你们是一帮盗墓贼。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) unsheathes a knife from his belt\./, "$1 从腰带上拽出一把小刀。");
	text = text.replace("The watchman unsheathes a bell from his own belt, a large, rotund instrument that glistens gold on the side of the lantern\'s light and white on the side of the moon\'s.", "巡逻者则从腰带上拽出一个硕大的铜铃，一面反射着烛火，一面反射着月光。");
	text = text.replace("Come after me ye may, but not before I give this here bell a good ringing.", "你可以跟我来，但在我敲响这钟之前。");
	text = text.replace("Then the next bell you\'ll hear shall toll for thee.", "或者你会听到的我敲响警钟。");
	text = text.replace(/You grab (.*?) by the collar and tell him to leave\./, "你拽住 $1 的领子叫他快跑。");
	text = text.replace("There\'s no sense in causing trouble.", "没必要自找麻烦。");
	text = text.replace("The watchman barks at you as you depart.", "在你俩撒腿狂奔之际，看守朝你大吼。");
	text = text.replace("I\'ll remember yer faces!", "我记住你的长相了！");
	text = text.replace("Like a kicked dog knows the boot that done did it, I\'ll remember yer faces!", "就像被踢的狗知道是靴子干的，我会记得你的脸！");

//graverobber_vs_gravedigger_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/After burying a dead comrade, (.*?) pitches his shovel into the earth and grabs (.*?) by his tunic, driving him backward as he lifts him into the air\./, "在安葬了一位死去的战友之后，$1 丢下铲子，揪着 $2 的领子把他推开。");
	text = text.replace("Before even a word or threat can be exchanged, the dangling man throws a kick into his attacker\'s groin.", "还没来得及开口骂上几句，那还没站稳的家伙就对着攻击自己的人的胯下来了一脚。");
	text = text.replace("They both fall to the ground and immediately start tumbling about in the mud.", "他俩一起摔倒在地，在泥地里打架。");
	text = text.replace("The muck makes them indistinguishable, but their fit of anger is well heard.", "俩人身上都沾满了泥土，看上去一模一样，又开始骂起来。");
	text = text.replace("The gravedigger climbs on top of the graverobber and starts piling mud into his opponent\'s face.", "掘墓人压在盗墓贼身上，把手里的泥摔在他脸上。");
	text = text.replace("What\'d I tell ya, huh?", "我没跟你说过吗，哏？");
	text = text.replace("What\'d I say about thievin\' from those who can\'t see your grimy little hands comin\', huh?", "要是再让我看见你这个狗东西发死人财就怎么样，哏？");
	text = text.replace("With a nice little reversal that suggests this isn\'t his first time wrestling in the mud, the graverobber throws his assailant off and clambers atop him..", "盗墓贼熟练地一个翻身把对手掀翻在地，很明显他不是第一次这样在泥地里打滚了，然后爬到对手身上。");
	text = text.replace("He grabs great big piles of grass and grime and shoves it into the gravedigger\'s face.", "他连根揪起一大丛杂草，朝着掘墓人脸上掼去。");
	text = text.replace("Bizarrely, the graverobber thinks it\'s time to make his case.", "令人惊奇的是，盗墓贼开口反击了。");
	text = text.replace("It only be his shoes!", "那只是他的鞋！");
	text = text.replace("It only be his gloves!", "他的手套！");
	text = text.replace("Dead needn\'t be walkin\' or pickin\' things up, let \'em be mine I say!", "死人可用不着走路，也不用搬东西，给我用多好！");
	text = text.replace("Ah, it appears that the gravedigger and graverobber have come across a mild difference on what goes into the ground and what shant come back out.", "唉，看来掘墓人和盗墓贼对于哪些东西应该下葬，而哪些又该留在地面上这个问题的见解上有些许小小的不同。");
	text = text.replace("You let them work through their troubles - there is little harm to be done between the two of them and it is making good entertainment for the rest of the company, anyway.", "你由着他们打架－反正俩人都没受什么伤，反倒是给战队的其他人找了个乐子。");

//greedy_demands_raise_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) enters your tent with a scroll at his side\./, "$1 带着一小卷纸走进你的帐篷。");
	text = text.replace("He unfurls it, revealing a literal list of things he has killed.", "他把纸摊开，一一列举了他加入以来杀过的东西。");
	text = text.replace("You inquire as to what he wants you to do with that.", "你问他这是什么意思。");
	text = text.replace("The scroll is tossed onto your desk and he responds.", "他把那张纸按在你的办公桌上，回答。");
	text = text.replace(/Compensate me\. Higher pay starting right now\. (.*?) crowns a day\./, "补偿我。从现在开始提高工资。每天 $1 克朗。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) apparently wants higher pay, (.*?) crowns a day instead of the (.*?) crowns he earns now, stating that he has slain a great deal of enemies while in the company of the (.*?)\./, "$1 想要更高的工资，每天 $2 克朗，而不是现在的 $3 克朗，他的理由是在加入之后杀了不少敌人，都是为了 $4。");
	text = text.replace("Killing lots of things is a good bargaining chip when that\'s the business you are in, you\'ll give him that much.", "说实话，杀敌众多对你来说是个说得过去的理由，你或许会考虑给他涨工资。");
	text = text.replace(/It appears that (.*?) wants more pay on account of killing lots of, well, everything on your behalf\./, "看来，$1 想涨工资了，因为他为你杀了不少敌人。");
	text = text.replace("You tell him that none of it was on your personal behalf, just that you simply paid him to do it. He nods.", "你告诉他，这些都不是为了你个人的利益，只是你付钱让他这么做。他点头。");
	text = text.replace(/Right\. And now I want more pay\. (.*?) crowns a day\./, "好吧，那我希望现在你能多给我点。每天 $1 克朗。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) feels as though his services for the company aren\'t being well compensated\./, "$1 认为自己对战队的服务没有得到公平的报酬。");
	text = text.replace(/He\'s asking for more pay, (.*?) crowns a day instead of the (.*?) crowns he earns now, on account of how good he is at that whole mercenary business\./, "他要求更高的工资，每天 $1 克朗，而不是现在的 $2 克朗，理由是他精通于做一位雇佣兵。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) is demanding you pay him more, (.*?) crowns a day instead of the (.*?) crowns he earned so far, now that he has proven himself more than capable of fighting for the (.*?)\./, "$1 向你要求更高的工资，每天 $2 克朗，而不是现在的 $3 克朗，他认为自己已经向大家证明了自己的实力，在 $4。");
	text = text.replace("He\'s got a bit of a point, though you\'re not sure you\'re ready to hand the crowns over quite yet.", "他给出的理由合情合理，只是你不知道自己究竟愿不愿意多给点钱。");
	
	text = text.replace(/You agree to (.*?)\'s terms\./, "你同意了 $1的条件。");
	text = text.replace("He\'s very unsurprisingly happy about it and you get on with your day.", "他无疑十分高兴，这一天平淡的过去了。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?)\'s demands aren\'t too much and you are happy to fork him a few extra crowns a day\./, "$1的要求并不高，于是你也就同意每天多给他几块钱。");
	text = text.replace("He gives you a handshake.", "他和你握了手。");
	text = text.replace("It\'s firm, but not too firm.", "很坚定，但又没那么热情。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) wavers on his feet as he readies for your answer\./, "$1 紧张的等待你的回答。");
	text = text.replace("You tell him to relax as you\'ve agreed to his terms.", "你叫他放松，因为你已经同意了他的要求。");
	text = text.replace("He finally sighs in relief.", "他发出一声舒缓的叹息。");
	text = text.replace("Thank you, sir. I thought I might have to, I dunno.", "谢谢你，先生。我还以为我得用，呃。");
	//text = text.replace("You raise an eyebrow.", "你挑挑眉毛。");
	text = text.replace("I hope that wasn\'t a threat.", "这不是在威胁我吧。");
	text = text.replace("The man awkwardly laughs and shakes his head.", "他尴尬地笑笑，摇头。");
	text = text.replace("No, no of course not!", "不，当然不是了！");
	text = text.replace(/You tell (.*?) you\'ll increase his pay under one condition: he do a little dance\./, "你告诉 $1 工资要涨，只要他为你做一件事：跳一支舞。");
	text = text.replace("A victory dance?", "一支胜利的舞？");
	//text = text.replace("You shrug.", "你耸肩。");
	text = text.replace("Any dance.", "跳什么舞都行。");
	text = text.replace("He raises his arms and swings them a little.", "他举起双手，甩了几下。");
	text = text.replace("You burst into laughter.", "你笑了出来。");
	text = text.replace("No number of kills would amount to whatever that was.", "杀多少人也没有这个管用啊。");
	text = text.replace("The man snickers.", "他笑笑。");
	//text = text.replace("Thank you, sir.", "谢谢你，先生。");
	text = text.replace(/You agree to give (.*?) a higher wage\./, "你同意给 $1 涨工资了。");
	text = text.replace("It would be my privilege.", "太感谢了。");
	text = text.replace("The man raises an eyebrow.", "他挑了挑眉毛。");
	text = text.replace("Spare me the ceremony.", "别管那些礼节了。");
	text = text.replace("I\'m here to kill, let\'s not dance around it.", "咱们干这行是杀人的，不是围着它跳舞。");
	//text = text.replace("You nod.", "你点头。");
	
	text = text.replace(/You decline (.*?)\'s request\./, "你拒绝了 $1的要求。");
	text = text.replace("He purses his lips, wrings his hands, then nods, turns and leaves.", "他抿着嘴唇，握紧拳头，点了一下头，然后走出帐篷。");
	text = text.replace("The silence is a bit harsh, but the message well received: he ain\'t a happy man.", "虽然一个字也没说，不过你明白了他的意思：他不开心了。");
	text = text.replace(/Declining (.*?)\'s request leads to a sudden outburst\./, "拒绝了 $1的要求，他一下就愤怒了。");
	text = text.replace("Well, fark this shit.", "去你的吧。");
	text = text.replace("I\'ll still fight fer ya, but don\'t expect the best out of me!", "我还是会帮你打仗，不过你可想好了，别想让我出死力气！");
	text = text.replace("You nod, but tell him he\'d be dead without putting forth his best, so you\'ll get what you want regardless.", "你点头，不过告诉他如果他不拼死作战的话，终究还是免不了一死，所以说这于你没有损失。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) winces when you decline the suggestion\./, "$1 的要求被你拒绝后，他很明显颤抖了一下。");
	text = text.replace("Alright then, I see how this place is run.", "好吧，我知道这地方是怎么运作的了。");
	text = text.replace("In we go, out we go.", "我们替你出生入死。");
	text = text.replace("No matter to you, right?", "这都不管你啥事，是这样吧？");
	text = text.replace("We\'re just the pawns you use to get what you want.", "我们就是你棋盘上的小卒子，你的工具。");
	text = text.replace("That\'s fine. That\'s absolutely fine.", "好吧。没关系。");
	text = text.replace("He turns and leaves.", "他转身走了。");
	text = text.replace("You get the feeling it is not at all \'fine.\'", "你感觉他话里有刺。");
	text = text.replace(/You tell (.*?) that you do not agree with his estimations of how much he should get paid\./, "你告诉 $1 你不同意他对他应该得到多少报酬的估计。");
	text = text.replace("He responds with a few swears with an estimated volume of \'loud.\' When he\'s finished, he nods.", "他骂了几句脏话，声音估计“很大”。等骂完了，他点头。");
	text = text.replace("But that\'s alright. I get the business.", "没关系。我明白，你得挣钱。");
	text = text.replace("And I\'m sure you understand that you get why I must look after the business that is myself, too.", "不过也希望你能明白，我也得挣钱。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) presses for more pay, but you put your foot down\./, "$1 要求加薪，但你坚决不同意。");
	text = text.replace("You\'ll get what we agreed upon, no more.", "我们之前商量好了给你多少钱，就是多少。");
	text = text.replace("He nods and then slowly back out of the tent.", "他点头，慢慢走出你的帐篷。");
	text = text.replace("As you say, sir.", "听你的，先生。");

//hedge_knight_vs_raider_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) is sitting out beside the campfire, his eyes set deep into the flames\./, "$1 坐在篝火旁边，他的眼神深深地盯着火焰。");
	text = text.replace("A few moments ago, a couple of the men were heard yelling at him.", "不久之前，几个人曾经朝着他吼过一顿。");
	text = text.replace("A past as a raider isn\'t winning the man many friends.", "作为一个掠夺者，此人很明显得罪过不少人。");
	text = text.replace(/The hedge knight, (.*?), walks over and stands there beside him\./, "雇佣骑士，$1 走到他身边站着。");
	text = text.replace("As the two exchange glances, you\'re suddenly worried a fight you can\'t stop is going to break out.", "两人互相瞥了一眼，你还以为他们俩要打上一架。");
	text = text.replace("Instead, the hedge knight takes a seat.", "结果，雇佣骑士却坐下了。");
	text = text.replace("He speaks calmly, though his deep voice is still soundly scary.", "他平静地开口，不过他深沉的声音还是充满了威慑力。");
	text = text.replace("You raided coasts, yes?", "你以前曾经驾着长船掠夺海岸，是吧？");
	text = text.replace("Killed women and children?", "屠杀女人和孩子？");
	text = text.replace("Stole from the clergy?", "从教士手里抢东西？");
	text = text.replace("The raider nods.", "掠夺者点头。");
	text = text.replace("Aye, and worse.", "嗯，还有更多更坏的事。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) picks up a chunk of smoldering wood from the fire\./, "$1 从火堆里捞出一块冒着火的焦炭。");
	text = text.replace("He crushes it in his hand, the flames hissing into ash and smoke.", "用两只空手碾得粉碎，火焰熄灭了，变成烟与灰烬。");
	text = text.replace("He lets it crumble out of a calloused palm.", "他松开手，抖落那些灰渣。");
	text = text.replace("You shouldn\'t mind what others say, raider.", "别理那些人说的话，掠夺者。");
	text = text.replace("This is a nasty, hungry world, and you mind its teeth well.", "这是一个肮脏、饥饿的世界，而你从它的利齿下活了下来。");
	text = text.replace("Let the weak cry out and die.", "让那些弱者哭叫着丧命吧。");
	text = text.replace("We can only armor ourselves by our very being, wreathed in the envy of the dead who would gladly crush an infant\'s skull for a mere sip of the breath our lungs draw.", "我们能做的只有穿好铠甲，面对那些吃婴儿的饥渴的死者，它们可想要我们的命呢。");
	text = text.replace("The raider grabs his own chunk of firewood and grinds it up.", "掠夺者也拿起一块火炭，把它捏碎。");
	text = text.replace("They shake hands and say nothing more.", "两个人最后握了一下手，再未发一言。");

//hedgeknight_vs_hedgeknight_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) sprints into your tent, nearly taking out one of the stakes and bringing the whole thing down\./, "$1 急着投胎似的冲进你的大帐，在固定桩上绊了一跤，险些把整个帐篷都扯倒。");
	text = text.replace("Sweat flies off his face and onto your maps.", "豆大的汗珠不住地从他脸上滴下，打湿了你的地图。");
	text = text.replace("You look at the man with a stare that demands a good answer for what he\'s doing.", "你盯着他，让他解释一下这整的是哪一出。");
	text = text.replace(/He explains that the hedge knights (.*?) and (.*?) are getting into it\./, "他忙说 $1 和 $2 那俩雇佣骑士闹起来了。");
	text = text.replace("They\'ve both picked up weapons and look about ready to kill each other.", "两人都抄着家伙，看架式多半是要玩命。");
	text = text.replace("Having the two largest men in the company do battle probably isn\'t best for the health of... well, everyone.", "让队里块头最大的两个家伙打上一场对你甚至是对整个团队而言可都不是件…好事。");
	text = text.replace("You quickly rush to the scene.", "你连忙赶去现场。");
	
	text = text.replace(/You find (.*?) with a great sword in hand and (.*?) is twirling a giant axe around like a child would a stick\./, "只见 $1 紧紧握着一把大剑，$2 如小孩耍木棍般舞着一柄巨斧。");
	text = text.replace(/Most of the men have cleared out. (.*?) explains that the two/, "其他队友都躲在一旁不敢上前。$1 解释说他俩");
	text = text.replace("have unfinished business from a jousting tournament", "之前在一场骑枪比赛里没分出胜负");
	text = text.replace("met before on the battlefield, on opposite sides, and now look to continue a battle long past", "之前在战场上交过手，现在还想再分个高下");
	text = text.replace("seek to end a dispute between them by the old tradition of mortal combat", "起了点矛盾，不断加剧最终升级成了真人快打");
	text = text.replace(/Another brother steps forward, begging that the hedge knights put their differences aside, but (.*?) throws him out of the way\./, "一位兄弟站了出来，恳求他俩放下隔阂，却被 $1 一把推开。");
	text = text.replace("Golems of might and terror that they are, perhaps it is wise to seek an end to this confrontation?", "鉴于他俩不像能劝得动，或许让他俩一劳永逸的解决矛盾才是上策？");
	
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) calls out to you, asking you to stop the fight\./, "$1 请求你阻止这场争斗。");
	text = text.replace("The two hedge knights look over, each breath heaving their massive chests.", "两个雇佣骑士把视线转向你，壮硕的胸膛上下起伏。");
	text = text.replace("You throw a dismissive hand.", "你无动于衷。");
	text = text.replace("The knights nod and charge one another.", "他们微微点头，随后向对方发起猛冲。");
	text = text.replace("The clash is loud, metal-shattering, bone-crunching.", "金铁相交，碰撞声不绝于耳。");
	text = text.replace("Growls follow every attempt to kill, so sonorous become the weapon swings.", "两人咆哮着试图杀死对方，声音之洪亮已经隐隐盖过了兵刃的破空声。");
	text = text.replace("The sword catches the shaft of the giant axe and the two blades snap against one another.", "这把剑切住了巨大斧头的柄，两刃相互咬合。");
	text = text.replace("The hedge knights exchange cruel stares over the crossing, then quickly disarm and pull daggers, stabbing each other repeatedly as they fall to the ground.", "他们恶狠狠地对视一眼，不约而同地掏出匕首，一下又一下地猛扎对方，直至一同摔倒在地。");
	text = text.replace("Neither man seems the least bit bothered by the wounds.", "看来哪怕是遍体鳞伤也不足以让这两头人形怪物停止争斗。");
	text = text.replace("They give up on the pitiful daggers and turn to using their own mitts, punching each other so fiercely you see teeth scattering amongst the bloodsprays.", "武器很快又从匕首换成了带着护套的拳头，鲜血与碎齿四下飞溅。");
	text = text.replace("Again, the company looks to you for guidance as it is becoming readily obvious that these men seek to fight to a finish.", "队员们再次向你投来求助的眼神，显然，若不出手干预，这场争斗必定会以一位雇佣骑士的死亡收场。");
	
	text = text.replace("The two hedge knights stand there, eyes only on their opponent and with no regard to your words, each breath heaving their massive chests.", "两个雇佣骑士对你的劝阻充耳不闻，只是死死盯着对方，壮硕的胸膛上下起伏。");
	text = text.replace("A short moment and they charge one another.", "少顷，他们向对方发起猛冲。");
	text = text.replace("The clash is loud, metal-shattering, bone-crunching.", "金铁相交，碰撞声不绝于耳。");
	text = text.replace("Growls follow every attempt to kill, so sonorous become the weapon swings.", "两人咆哮着试图杀死对方，声音之洪亮已经隐隐盖过了兵刃的破空声。");
	text = text.replace("The sword catches the shaft of the giant axe and the two blades snap against one another.", "这把剑切住了巨大斧头的柄，两刃相互咬合。");
	text = text.replace("The hedge knights exchange cruel stares over the crossing, then quickly disarm and pull daggers, stabbing each other repeatedly as they fall to the ground.", "他们恶狠狠地对视一眼，不约而同地掏出匕首，一下又一下地猛扎对方，直至一同摔倒在地。");
	text = text.replace("Neither man seems the least bit bothered by the wounds.", "看来哪怕是遍体鳞伤也不足以让这两头人形怪物停止争斗。");
	text = text.replace("They give up on the pitiful daggers and turn to using their own mitts, punching each other so fiercely you see teeth scattering amongst the bloodsprays.", "武器很快又从匕首换成了带着护套的拳头，鲜血与碎齿四下飞溅。");
	text = text.replace("The company looks to you for guidance as it is becoming readily obvious that these men seek to fight to a finish.", "队员们再次向你投来求助的眼神，显然，若不出手干预，这场争斗必定会以一位雇佣骑士的死亡收场。");
	
	text = text.replace("You bring out a satchel heavy with coins.", "你掏出一袋沉甸甸的硬币。");
	text = text.replace("The two hedge knights look over, the sound of gold clinking against itself hard to miss.", "两个雇佣骑士转过头来，金子相互碰撞的声音吸引了他们的注意。");
	text = text.replace("A thousand crowns to each of you, yeah?", "一人一千克朗，怎么样？");
	text = text.replace("The men exchange a glance.", "他们交换了一眼。");
	text = text.replace("They shrug. You nod.", "他们耸耸肩。你点头。");
	text = text.replace("Alright, but this isn\'t happening again, understand?", "下不为例，明白吗？");
	text = text.replace("The men nod too, walking over and accepting the crowns with shameless ease.", "他们也点头，接过了这一大笔简直是天上掉下来的横财。");
	text = text.replace("Some brothers look a little miffed that these men just got free money for essentially choosing not to fight.", "其他兄弟们嫉妒得眼都红了，可能没想到打个架还有钱可拿。");
	text = text.replace("The hedge knights begrudgingly find peace amongst themselves, being more concerned with counting money than killing each other.", "终于，两位雇佣骑士一致同意比起斗个你死我活，还是钱来得实在。");
	text = text.replace("You just hope they got an equal amount lest the \'festivities\' resume.", "你只希望他们不会因为分赃不均而又“庆祝”一场。");
	
	text = text.replace("Having seen enough, you order the men to intervene.", "你看够了，忙叫队员们去中止这场战斗。");
	text = text.replace("They hesitate, but you quickly remind them of their contractual duties.", "队员们犹豫了，但你搬出雇佣合同上的条款劝服了他们。");
	text = text.replace("The men grab great tarps of leather and blankets and some pots and pans and a few carry buckets.", "他们拿来了大块的皮革和毯子还有各种锅碗瓢盆。");
	text = text.replace("Their strategy is sound: buckets are slammed over the heads of the hedge knights, blinding them just long enough to throw everything else over them.", "计划很简单：把这堆东西一股脑全扣在两个雇佣骑士身上，趁他俩蒙圈的时候上去把他俩拉开。");
	text = text.replace("As a man would wrestle a bull, the men tangle with the hedge knights, occasionally being thrown into the air, and one brother eats a kick to the face, suffering a black-gapped smile for his troubles.", "但接下来的情况就像斗牛一样，男人们和雇佣骑士们纠缠在一起，有人被掀翻到空中、有人被一脚踹了个满脸开花。");
	text = text.replace("Another is swallowed up in the mass of blankets, being smashed in between the growling hedge knights like an amorphous blob of anger.", "甚至还有倒霉蛋被两个骑士夹在中间暴揍。");
	text = text.replace("Eventually, the two men cool down and the battle is over.", "终于，两位当事人消了气，给这场混乱画上了句号。");
	text = text.replace("They begrudgingly make peace, lest you have the rest of your men pick up real weapons to end the scuffle.", "若是再晚一点，只怕所有人都要抄起武器了。");
	text = text.replace("The rest of the company recovers, picking themselves up as though a great tornado had just torn through the camp.", "鼻青脸肿的队员们缓缓地爬起来，像是刚被台风刮过一般。");
	text = text.replace("You take account of the injuries and begin distributing aid.", "你连忙清点受伤的人数并为他们做紧急处理。");
	
	text = text.replace("You set yourself down on a stump and watch the rest of the fight.", "你找了一截树桩坐下观赏这场战斗。");
	text = text.replace("The men roll around on the ground, smashing each other in the face with punches that would kill a horse.", "两人在地上滚来滚去，用足以打死一匹马的力道猛击对方的脸。");
	text = text.replace(/Eventually, (.*?) squats on (.*?)\'s shoulders\./, "最终，$1 压在 $2的肩膀上。");
	text = text.replace(/Seeing a rock nearby, (.*?) grabs it and cracks it over his opponent\'s skull\./, "$1 见旁边有块大石头，便一把拿过来砸在对手的头上。");
	text = text.replace("A bit of flesh is sheared off, revealing a slop of red and white beneath.", "血肉模糊，隐隐露出了一些红白之物。");
	text = text.replace("The rock is brought down again.", "好石头举起又砸下的。");
	text = text.replace(/The brain pan splinters, shards of bone rupturing into fragments\. (.*?) goes a bit limp, showing only a modicum of fight left in him\. (.*?) punches his fist into the brainbox and rips out the namesake in one big gush of crimson\./, "头盖骨砸成碎片，$1 已经没了反击的力气。$2 将拳头捣进头骨并掏出了一团猩红的东西。");
	text = text.replace("You gag at the sight, and a few men turn and vomit.", "你捂住了嘴，有几个队员直接转过身吐了一地。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) gets to his feet and throws his trophy into the tall grass\./, "$1 摇摇晃晃地起身，扔掉手中的那团东西。");
	text = text.replace("He wipes his forehead and says only one word.", "擦了擦满头满脸的血，只说了一个词。");
	text = text.replace("Finished.", "完事。");
	
	text = text.replace(/You look to set yourself down on a nearby stump but jump back when the two hedge knights come barreling your way\. (.*?)\'s head smashes face first into what was to be your seat\./, "你刚在一截树桩上坐下又立马起身，才不至于被打过来的两个骑士给波及到。$1的脸磕在你刚才坐着的地方。");
	text = text.replace("He quickly turns around to face his assailant.", "他迅速转身面对袭击他的人。");
	text = text.replace(/All he meets is (.*?)\'s boot, the interfacing of flesh and leather sounding off with a sickening clap\./, "却被 $1的靴子正中面门，皮革与血肉碰撞发出一声钝响。");
	text = text.replace(/Now gargling on his own teeth, (.*?) asks if that\'s the best (.*?)\'s got\./, "$1 咽下被打落的牙齿，嘲笑 $2 是不是只有这点本事。");
	text = text.replace(/To answer, (.*?) kicks him in the head again and again, and each rearing of his boot reveals (.*?) to be in a worse state, from bloodied red to a nightmarish twisting of flesh and eyelids and a flattened nose and a grin of horror where his teeth are either missing or hanging from blood engorged gums like they were nails on a skinless finger\./, "$1 猛踢他的脸作为回答，每次抬起他的靴子，就会发现 $2 的人处于更糟糕的状态，从血淋淋的红色到像噩梦般扭曲的肉体和眼睑，扁平的鼻子和恐怖的笑容，他的牙齿要么不见了，要么挂在充血的牙龈上，就像脱皮手指上的钉子。");
	text = text.replace("Finally, the brainpan is crushed, the series of splintering boneplates sounding like something falling through a winter tree\'s branches.", "终于，脑壳不堪重负，发出的一连串碎裂声好似冬日里结霜的树枝弯折发出的怪响。");
	text = text.replace("You turn your gaze in abhorrence, but some brothers cannot, one spews vomit.", "并非所有兄弟都像你一样有勇气看下去，甚至有人吐了。");
	text = text.replace(/Peeking to see what damage was done, you see (.*?)\'s heel is halfway down a throat and the toe of his boot is churning another man\'s brain\./, "只见 $1的靴子捣进了对手的脑子里。");
	text = text.replace("He curses as he struggles to retrieve what delivered the killing blow.", "他一边骂脏话一边挣扎着想将脚拔出来。");
	text = text.replace("The surviving hedge knight has to pull on his thigh to help yank his foot out of the brainpan.", "甚至得拽着大腿根方才将卡在脑壳里的脚给释放出来。");
	text = text.replace("Turning around, he drags his foot across the grass and picks his heel up like a child coming in after a day\'s play, looking intently to make sure there was no mess to be dragged in after him.", "他转过身，将脚在地上擦了又擦，并像在野外玩了一整天的孩子那样，把脚往后翘起以确认脚后跟没有沾上什么不干净的东西。");
	text = text.replace("He peels off a slug of brain matter and throws it aside like he just shucked some corn.", "靴子上还沾着一片大脑的碎块，他像剥玉米壳般轻描淡写地取下来并扔到一旁。");
	text = text.replace("Rubbing his belly, he asks if anyone\'s hungry before grabbing a plate of grits and heading back to his own tent.", "随后揉着肚子问大家饿不饿，并端着满满一大盘粗粮粥回了帐篷。");
	text = text.replace(/Later in the night, after you\'ve put down a short-lived plot to have the man eliminated for the safety of the company, you find (.*?) sleeping like a baby\./, "当晚，在考虑要不要为了团队的安全处理掉他时，你发现 $1 睡得宛如婴儿般香甜。");
	
	text = text.replace("The monk nods, stepping forward and calmly walking between the two men.", "僧侣点头，冷静地走上前拦在两人之间。");
	text = text.replace("His hands are raised, the fingers trailing to and fro as they mimic the shapes of old religious rites.", "他抬起手，摆出各种古老的宗教手势。");
	text = text.replace("He speaks of the gods and how they judge men for what they are and what they do.", "他开始讲述诸神如何根据人的本性和行为来评判世人。");
	text = text.replace("He says that some gods might find this battle favorable, but that most would not.", "有些神也许会认可这场争斗，但绝非大多数神。");
	text = text.replace("Most of all, though, the monk says that if they truly wish to fight, then there is plenty of room for that after they die.", "更重要的是，僧侣说，如果他们真的想战斗，两人大可死后在冥间尽情比武。");
	text = text.replace("However, if they kill one another, the loser is given great prestige in the afterlife, and the winner will not, for this violence serves no purpose than to give the victor pride.", "若选择在人世时争斗，被杀者将被神护佑送往来生，而杀人者则不会，这样的结果对于胜者毫无意义。");
	text = text.replace("Surprisingly, this oddity in religious rules calms the men down.", "令人惊讶的是，这些奇怪的宗教规矩似乎使两人冷静了下来。");
	text = text.replace("The monk invites them to talk more and they do so, the three walking off, hands gesticulating, backs arching in bellowing laughter.", "僧侣邀请两人进一步细谈，他们三个并排走着，拱着背，挥着手，谈笑风生。");
	text = text.replace("As for the rest of the company, they just seem happy nobody got killed.", "至于其他队员们，他们也挺高兴没闹出人命。");

//herbs_along_the_way_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/While heading toward your destination, (.*?) runs up to you with a bundle of herbs in hand\./, "在朝你的目的地进发的时候，$1 手里拿着一把草药向你跑来。");
	text = text.replace("Now you know this fool knows nothing about plants or wildlife, but he seems rather persistent in wanting to try them out.", "现在你知道这个傻蛋一点也不了解植物和野生动物，但他似乎非常执着地想要试一试它们。");
	text = text.replace("Something about \'hearing\' of magical powers to be found in the essence of herbs.", "大概什么“听说”草药的精华中蕴含着神奇的魔力。");
	text = text.replace("This talk gets the attention of a few others in the company.", "这个话题引起了战队里其他的伙伴的注意。");
	text = text.replace("Soon, a number of them are asking to try out the \'medicine\' for the good of their brothers.", "不久之后，为了队伍里的兄弟的身体，一些人开始要求尝试一下这些“药物”。");
	
	text = text.replace(/It appears that the herbs are not just harmless, but rather even proactive in taking care of some nagging issues with the men\. (.*?)\'s cold seems to have lifted, and the stomach pains of (.*?) have abated\./, "似乎这些草药不仅没有危害，甚至在处理兄弟们身上一些麻烦的疾病时很有效。$1的感冒好多了，$2 的胃痛也减轻了不少。");
	text = text.replace("After trying some yourself, you see a splinter wiggle its way out of your thumb. Amazing!", "在你自己尝试的时候，你甚至看见了一个小东西扭动着从你的大拇指中钻出来。神奇！");
	
	text = text.replace("From one end comes vomit and from the other shite.", "一个伙计开始呕吐起来，而另一个开始拉肚子。");
	text = text.replace(/It appears the herbs were not worth a try after all\. (.*?) bravely elected himself ready to chow down on the mystery plants and, suffice it to say, the proportions which you are seeing come out of him are definitely mystical in that strange, \'can the body really hold that much\?\', sort of way\./, "尝试这种草药似乎是一个错误的决定。$1 勇敢地吃下了大量的这种奇怪的植物，然后，这么说吧，你看见他又吐又泄地排出来的东西多得吓人，“人的身体里能容纳这么多东西吗？”,搞不懂。");

//hidden_cache_forest_event.nut
	text = text.replace("The forest is no friend of man which is why men of ill-repute sure love to put their keepsakes there.", "森林并非人类的好朋友，因此，很多声名狼藉的人喜欢在森林里藏东西。");
	text = text.replace(/And today you\'ve stumbled across one: a cache that (.*?) found by way of stubbing his toe on the edge of it\./, "今天你就偶然发现了一个：$1 的脚趾踢中了它的表面，从而发现了一个储藏处。");
	text = text.replace("Digging out the crate and cracking it open, you find an assortment of weapons, armor, and gold.", "你们挖出了一个板条箱，用力地把它敲开，发现里面藏了各种各样的武器和盔甲，还有不少黄金。");
	text = text.replace("You clap the sellsword on the shoulder and thank him for his \'hard work\'.", "你拍了拍发现那些东西的佣兵的肩膀并感谢他的“努力工作”。");
	text = text.replace("He wags his boot around.", "他晃了晃他的靴子。");
	text = text.replace("Yessir, I\'ve got a toe like the nose of a bloodhound.", "是的，先生，我有一个猎犬鼻子一般的脚趾头。");
	
	text = text.replace(/As you get ready to leave, (.*?) the graverobber stops you\./, "在你准备离开的时候，盗墓贼 $1 叫住了你。");
	text = text.replace("Wait a minute.", "等一下。");
	text = text.replace("He jumps down into the pit in which the cache was buried.", "他跳进了那个曾经埋着藏匿物的坑里。");
	text = text.replace("He starts knocking around on the dirt.", "他开始在那里的地上四处走动。");
	text = text.replace("Tap. Tap. Tap. Clack.", "哒。哒。哒。咔嚓。");
	text = text.replace("His knuckle raps hard and a smile crosses his face.", "他的手指用力敲着，随即露出了一个微笑。");
	text = text.replace("Yeah, that\'s what I thought.", "是的，跟我想的一样。");
	text = text.replace("The man digs into the earth and drags out another crate and opens it up.", "他向下又挖了挖，找到了另一个箱子并打开了它。");
	text = text.replace("You\'re wowed by the sight of what\'s inside. The graverobber nods.", "你为你所看见的东西而惊讶。盗墓贼点了点头。");
	text = text.replace("If someone has something good to hide, they don\'t just hide it in the ground, they hide it with things of lesser value.", "如果有人想藏一些好东西，他不仅仅将它藏在地下，他还会把它和一些没那么珍贵的东西藏在一起。");
	text = text.replace("That way, even if you find their treasure there\'s still a chance you\'ll get distracted from the real good stuff.", "这样就算你找到了他们藏的财宝，也很有可能找不到真正珍贵的东西。");
	text = text.replace("Quite clever, really, but it don\'t fool me none.", "很聪明，但是它糊弄不了我。");

//historian_mysterious_text_event.nut
	text = text.replace("You come across an abandoned chapel.", "你遇见了一个被遗弃的小教堂。");
	text = text.replace("Cobwebs dress its cracks, and bird nests the corners.", "蜘蛛们在它的裂缝处结网，鸟儿们在它的角落里筑巢。");
	text = text.replace("The pews are tipped over or have been chopped up for firewood.", "里面的座位要么翻倒在地，要么已经被劈开做了柴火。");
	text = text.replace("The old gods have surely left this place.", "那些古老的神明肯定已经放弃了这个地方。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) the historian comes to you with what look like muddy logs in his hands\./, "$1 这个历史学家手里拿着一份布满灰尘的稿件来到了你的身边。");
	text = text.replace("Would you look at this? Old scripts!", "你能看看这个吗？古老的手稿！");
	text = text.replace("He blows the blackened dust and ash off the scrolls.", "他吹开卷轴上已经变黑的泥土和灰尘。");
	text = text.replace("Have you ever seen something so spectacular?", "你见过这么令人惊叹的东西吗？");
	text = text.replace("I don\'t know what they say yet, but it\'s still a most interesting of finds!", "虽然我还不知道里面写了什么，但是这是一个非常有趣的发现！");
	text = text.replace("Right, whatever.", "好吧，随便了。");
	
	text = text.replace(/As you make camp outside the temple, (.*?) the historian enters your tent\./, "在你在神殿外宿营的时候，历史学家 $1 走进了你的帐篷。");
	text = text.replace("Sir, I think you might be interested in this.", "先生，我觉得你可能会对这个感兴趣。");
	text = text.replace("He\'s got the scrolls from the chapel in his arms and unravels a few of them across your desk.", "他把从教堂里找到的卷轴夹在胳膊里，然后将一些展开在你的办公桌上。");
	text = text.replace("There you see the historian\'s sloppy scribblings.", "在那些卷轴上面你看到了历史学家潦草的字迹。");
	text = text.replace("His notes are in a language you can\'t read, but you can easily follow the arrows he\'s drawn over the pages to connect segments together.", "他的笔记是用一种你看不懂的语言写的，但是你可以轻松地通过他在文章里划的箭头将不同的段落联系在一起。");
	text = text.replace("He then unfurls another scroll, a fresh one, with all the translations.", "接着他展开了另一个卷轴，一个崭新的，对所有内容进行了翻译的卷轴。");
	text = text.replace("These are old training manuals.", "这些是古老的训练手册。");
	text = text.replace("They speak of techniques I never knew existed.", "他们谈到了一些我从没听过的技术。");
	text = text.replace("Shall I disperse them amongst the men?", "我应不应该把他们在伙计们之间推广开来？");
	
	text = text.replace(/While sitting in your tent outside the abandoned temple, (.*?) the historian enters in a manner best described as reluctant\./, "在你坐在这个被遗弃的神殿外的帐篷里的时候，历史学家 $1 不情愿地走进了你的帐篷。");
	text = text.replace("In his hands are the scrolls he found in the chapel a few days back.", "在他的手里拿着几天之前他在小教堂里发现的那些卷轴。");
	text = text.replace("Sir, uh, the scrolls... they were most interesting.", "先生，呃，这些卷轴…它们很有趣。");
	text = text.replace("Bored, you inquire as to \'how interesting.\' The man explains.", "你无聊地问了问它究竟有多“有趣”。他解释道。");
	text = text.replace("Well, they\'ve been written in a very ancient language.", "呃，它们是用一种非常古老的语言写的。");
	text = text.replace("I\'m not well versed in it, but I can certainly read portions here and there.", "我对它不是很擅长，但是我能清楚地读懂这部分和那部分。");
	text = text.replace("You ask him what he wants then.", "你问他接下来想干什么。");
	text = text.replace("I\'d like to read the scrolls, but I could use a little bit of confidence before I do.", "我想继续阅读这些卷轴，但是我现在不太敢继续读下去了。");
	text = text.replace("Would you grace the reading?", "你能祝福这些文章吗？");
	text = text.replace("That is what my old professors would do before any great undertaking.", "那是我的老师在做任何大事之前都会做的事。");
	
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) picks up the scrolls\./, "$1 拿起了卷轴。");
	text = text.replace("He licks his lips, clears his throat, and begins to read aloud.", "他舔了舔他的嘴唇，清了清他的喉咙，然后大声地朗读起来。");
	text = text.replace("The words that come forth are not ones you\'d easily recognize.", "从他嘴里传出的词语你无法轻易的辨认。");
	text = text.replace("They sound so lazily produced as though he were a man being wrangled from a deep sleep, and indeed bringing with him the monsters that would inhabit the dreamworlds.", "它们听起来是如此的懒散，使得他就像一个刚刚从沉睡中被吵醒的人一样，而且还带来了那些栖息在梦境里的怪物。");
	text = text.replace("He stops and looks up.", "他停了下来然后向上看去。");
	text = text.replace("That was it. Do you feel anything?", "就是这样。你感觉到什么了吗？");
	text = text.replace("You raise an eyebrow.", "你抬了抬一边的眉毛。");
	text = text.replace("Feel anything? Why would--", "感觉到什么？为什么要－");
	text = text.replace("Madness. You see a spiraling darkness wreathed in living shadows, the screaming specters of creatures that still yet yearn for finality in death, and amongst them swirl beings, grinning and yapping, like bestial puppet masters, maws slipped to yonder depths, their boned teeth the only light in this realm, their smiles but crescents of ill-shaped moons come to feast on the stars themselves.", "疯狂。你看见一团螺旋形的暗影盘旋在一处活跃的阴影里：那些渴求死亡的生物的尖啸幽灵，在这些螺旋形的怪物中，面容狰狞，嘶叫狂吼，就像残忍的木偶的主人，咽喉幽邃而深远，他们剔除着这个邻域里仅剩的光芒，他们微笑着的但是畸变的新月形月亮开始吞噬它们自己。");
	text = text.replace("Oh naive one, does thou think Davkul does not listen?", "无知的凡人，汝可认为达库尔未曾听见？");
	text = text.replace(/You suddenly awake to (.*?)\'s screams\./, "你突然被 $1的尖叫惊醒。");
	text = text.replace("He says all manner of monsters are afoot.", "他说各种各样的怪物已经在准备了。");
	text = text.replace("With not a moment to waste you go to warn the men before all the hells and those not yet known can break loos.", "毫不犹豫地，你跑去警告你的伙计们，在地狱和那些未知的生物还未摆脱束缚之前。");
	
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) picks up the scroll and begins to read\./, "$1 拿起了卷轴并开始朗读起来。");
	text = text.replace("The language is at both familiar and yet primordially ancient.", "这种语言听起来即让人熟悉又感觉非常的古老。");
	text = text.replace("It tickles the ear like the scratch of vipers over sand and by no means any less threatening.", "它听起来让人耳朵发痒，就像毒蛇在沙子上摩擦，而且有一种无法言说的恐惧感。");
	text = text.replace("When he\'s finished, the historian looks up.", "当他结束时，历史学家抬头看去。");
	text = text.replace("Feel anything?", "感觉到什么了吗？");
	text = text.replace("Suddenly a dark, yet soft hand wraps around the man from behind, curving down toward his loins.", "突然，一只漆黑的，柔软的手从他身后环绕住他，并且弯曲着伸向他的腰部。");
	text = text.replace("Oh, humans. We did not think you would survive this long, and indeed it has been long since our services were called upon.", "噢，人类。我们还以为你们存活不了这么久，自从我们签订契约以来，已经过去了如此漫长的时间。");
	text = text.replace("Lithe, hip-swaying creatures slip so lightly into the tent as though they were hardly more than the wind itself.", "轻柔的，飘忽不定的生物悄然滑进帐篷里，好像它们就是风本身一样。");
	text = text.replace("Outside, you can hear the murmur of the rest of the company being overcome by the seductive beings.", "在帐篷外，你听见战队的其他人被这些生物诱惑所发出的呢喃低语。");
	text = text.replace("One walks toward you, her shape flashing between all the women of your life, testing your response, and when your heart warms it settles on a young lady that once broke your heart.", "一个生物朝你走来，她的外形在你这一生所见过的所有女性中不断变化，并且测试着你的反应，在你心中一动的时候，她的外形确定在一个曾经打动了你的心的年轻姑娘。");
	text = text.replace("The succubus falls atop you.", "这个女妖从你头顶飘下。");
	text = text.replace("Don\'t mind me, human, this is for you. Relax.", "别在意我，人类，这是给你的奖励。放轻松。");
	text = text.replace("You let the pleasures wash over you.", "你放任愉悦感充斥着你的身体。");
	text = text.replace(/Immeasurable hours later you awake with your trousers down and (.*?) in the corner rubbing his head\./, "不知道多久之后，你醒了过来，发现下半身没有穿着裤子，而 $1 在角落里揉着他的头。");
	text = text.replace("They were so wonderful, but the scroll\'s gone.", "这真是太神奇了，但是卷轴却消失了。");
	text = text.replace("I think it burned up after I said the words.", "我认为它在我念出上面写着的内容之后就焚毁了。");
	text = text.replace("Oh by the old gods do I wish I remember what they said!", "噢，旧神啊，希望我还记得那上面写了什么！");

//historian_records_adventures_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/Carrying a leathered tome in hand, (.*?) shuffles into your tent\./, "手里拿着一本皮革封面的大部头著作，$1 步伐沉重地走进了你的帐篷。");
	text = text.replace("Without a word spoken he lays the book on the table and takes a step back.", "没有说一句话，他把书放在桌上，然后后退了一步。");
	text = text.replace("You set your quill pen down and ask what it is.", "你把你手里的羽毛笔放下，问道，这是什么。");
	text = text.replace("He says to open it.", "他说，打开它。");
	text = text.replace("Sighing, you open the book and come to find pages littered with names and events you know well.", "叹了一口气，你翻开书的封面，发现里面杂乱地写着一些你熟知的名字和事迹。");
	text = text.replace("It is a history of the company and its adventures.", "这是你战队的历史和曾经经历的冒险。");
	text = text.replace("You flip through the pages, seeing old tales that warm the heart and some that break it.", "你轻轻敲着书页，看着那些温暖心灵的、让人心碎的曾今。");
	text = text.replace("You close the book and push it back across the table.", "合上书籍，你把它推回桌上。");
	text = text.replace("The historian asks if it is alright, and you nod.", "历史学家问，还有什么需要修改的吗，你摇了摇头。");
	text = text.replace("You say give it to the men to read around camp for it will surely lift their spirits.", "你对历史学家说，把它给营地里的伙计们都读一读，它一定会鼓舞他们的精神。");

//houndmaster_tames_wolf_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/While traversing the snowy wastelands of the realm\'s north, (.*?) the houndmaster has come to befriend a creature that\'s been trailing beside the company\'s march: a wolf\./, "当你穿行在大雪覆盖着的北方王国荒僻之地时，训兽师 $1 准备与一个跟在战队之后行动的生物成为朋友：一只狼。");
	text = text.replace("The houndmaster frequently remained in the rearguard, crouched low, hands at his side, locking eyes with the lone wolf for minutes on end.", "驯兽师频繁地留在后卫中，伏低身子，双手放在身边，连续好几分钟盯着那只独狼不放。");
	text = text.replace("But today, using a bit of leftover meat, he plied the beast right into the middle of the camp.", "但是在今天，通过使用一些吃剩的肉，他成功地引诱那只狼走进了营地的中央。");
	text = text.replace("Now he squats at its side, dwarfed by its prominent, muscled withers, its pointed and attentive ears, and a lapping maw lined with mankilling canines.", "现在他蹲在它的身边，因为它那强壮又充满肌肉的身体，支楞着的敏锐耳朵，连着一个饥饿地蠕动着的胃的危险的犬齿而显得那么矮小。");
	text = text.replace("The rest of the men stand behind their weapons.", "其他的伙计们都站在他们的武器旁边。");
	text = text.replace("One yells at the houndmaster to stop what he is doing.", "一个人对驯兽师叫喊着让他快停下这危险的行为。");
	text = text.replace("Another says the wolf can smell fear.", "一些人说，狼可以嗅出恐惧的味道。");
	text = text.replace("Yet another throws a rock at it.", "另一些人则在对它扔石头。");
	text = text.replace("The wolf winces, but doesn\'t react.", "这只狼躲避着，但是没有任何回应。");
	text = text.replace("Laughing, the houndmaster makes a \'tssst!\' noise and points.", "哈哈大笑着，驯兽师吹了一声口哨“叮！”，指了指一个方向。");
	text = text.replace("The wolf launches forward, picking up the stone and bringing it back to the man.", "狼站起身来朝前跑去，叼起了石头然后把它带给了他。");
	text = text.replace("He rubs the beast\'s mane.", "他摸了摸兽毛。");
	text = text.replace("See, easily trained, just any dog.", "看到没，简单地训练之后，就像一只狗一样。");
	text = text.replace("Only bigger, faster, and stronger. Smarter, too.", "只是大了一些，快了一些，强壮了一些而已。当然，也更聪明了。");
	text = text.replace("Its eyes meet yours.", "它看了看你。");
	text = text.replace(/The wolf lays low, almost like a man bowing\. (.*?) laughs again\./, "那只狼低低地躺着，就像一个人在鞠躬一样。$1 又笑了笑。");
	text = text.replace("See? It already knows who is alpha of this pack.", "看到没？它还知道我们这些人里老大是谁。");

//how_far_is_the_sun_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/While resting, the men start a conversation about how far away the sun is\. (.*?) looks up at it, wincing and gritting his teeth as he just about blinds himself in his measuring\./, "在休息的时候，伙计们开启了一个关于太阳有多远的话题。$1 抬头看着，咬紧牙关、呲牙咧嘴地，在眼镜快被亮瞎之前完成了测量。");
	text = text.replace("Finally, he looks back down.", "最后，他低下头来。");
	text = text.replace("I\'d wager it\'s about ten to fifteen miles away.", "我敢打赌，它离我们大概十到十五英里远。");
	text = text.replace("He nods at his own presumably accurate summation.", "他在自认为非常正确的结论中点了点头。");
	text = text.replace("Aye, probably not even that far.", "没错，甚至可能没有那么远。");
	text = text.replace("I heard a story about an archer in a faraway land hitting it with an arrow.", "我听说过这么一个故事，在遥远的国度里甚至有个弓箭手用弓箭击中了太阳。");
	
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) the historian starts in on the conversation\./, "$1 历史学家开始加入这个话题。");
	text = text.replace("I doubt the veracity of that claim about shooting it with a bow.", "我对那个用弓射击的说法的真实性表示质疑。");
	text = text.replace("Here\'s a much more truthful tale I\'ve read of: there are men in the mountains of the east who have big spyglasses to stare up at the night sky.", "我曾读过一个更加真实的故事：在东方的大山中，有一群人用大型望远镜观测夜空。");
	text = text.replace("They think the sun is quite far away.", "他们认为太阳离我们非常远。");
	text = text.replace("At least ten thousand miles, even.", "甚至至少有一万英里远。");
	text = text.replace("They also think the nightlights are other suns and not the souls of dead heroes.", "他们还认为，群星是其他的太阳，而非已故英雄们的灵魂。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) gets up\./, "$1 站了起来。");
	text = text.replace("Watch yer mouth, fool, and don\'t speak ill of our ancestors.", "嘴上有点把门的，傻子，别说咱祖宗的坏话。");
	text = text.replace("The historian nods.", "历史学家点了点头。");
	text = text.replace("Of course! It was only an idea.", "当然这只是一个观点。");
	text = text.replace(/What hogwash\. Pretty dumb shite for a supposed \'smart\' man like (.*?)\. A few of the brothers have a laugh at the historian\'s silly notions\./, "狗屁，你这什么“聪明的” $1 就是一坨狗屎。其他兄弟开始嘲笑历史学家这个愚蠢的观点。");
	
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) the monk starts in on the conversation\./, "$1 僧侣开始加入这个话题。");
	text = text.replace("The sun is neither far nor close.", "太阳既不远也不近。");
	text = text.replace("It is the eye of many of the gods, the scope through which they use to watch over us.", "它是诸神之眼，是照向我们的诸神之镜。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) nods, but then, curious, asks about the moon\./, "$1 点了点头，然后好奇地问道，那月亮呢。");
	text = text.replace("The monk smiles confidently.", "僧侣自信地笑着。");
	text = text.replace("Do you think the gods would shine upon us for all hours?", "你认为诸神整天都照耀着我们？");
	text = text.replace("Of course they dim the lights a bit, to give us mortals a nice night to sleep in.", "他们当然要调低一点亮度，给我们这些凡人一个美好的夜晚来睡觉。");
	text = text.replace("You nod. Truly the old gods are always looking out for us.", "你点头。这些古老的神明一直在照顾着我们。");
	
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) the cultist gets up and looks at the sun\./, "$1 异教徒站了起来，看着太阳。");
	text = text.replace("As he continues to stare at it, a shadow slowly emerges over his face, as though some entity were shielding him from the light.", "在他注视着太阳的时候，一片阴影渐渐浮现在他的脸上，就好像有什么东西帮他遮住了阳光。");
	text = text.replace("Suddenly, he raises a hand and starts drawing some aerial rites with his hand.", "突然，他举起双手，开始在手上绘制一些宗教图案。");
	text = text.replace("You swear the darkness on his face is moving as though an imprint of his drawings, a sort of shifting tattoo.", "你敢发誓他脸上的阴影开始动了起来，就像他绘制的印记，一种移动的纹身。");
	text = text.replace("When he\'s finished, he takes a seat.", "当他结束之后，他坐了下来。");
	text = text.replace("The sun is dying.", "太阳正在死亡。");
	text = text.replace("The men look concerned. One interjects.", "伙计们很担心，一个人插嘴道。");
	text = text.replace("Dying? What do you mean?", "正在死亡？这话怎么说？");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) stares at him\./, "$1 盯着他。");
	text = text.replace("Davkul wills it that all may die.", "达库尔的意志一切终将消亡。");
	text = text.replace("One man asks if this supposed \'Davkul\' will die too. The cultist nods.", "一个人问这个所谓的“达库尔”是否也会死。异教徒点头。");
	text = text.replace("When there is nothing left to die, Davkul may finally rest.", "当万物消亡之后，达库尔便会陷入沉睡。");
	text = text.replace("A crueler god would have departed already.", "一个残酷的神将逝去。");
	text = text.replace("It is by Davkul\'s good graces that he will go last, and for that we praise him.", "达库尔的恩赐在于他将最后一个离去，这也是我们赞美他的地方。");
	
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) takes the challenge, grabbing his bow and a couple of arrows\./, "$1 拿出他的弓和一对箭，开始了尝试。");
	text = text.replace("He licks his finger and holds it up.", "舔了舔手指，他举起手来。");
	text = text.replace("Wind\'s right for a good star shootin\'.", "现在的风向正好适合来一箭。");
	text = text.replace("The archer nocks an arrow, draws, and takes aim.", "弓箭手搭上一只箭，拉紧弓弦，然后瞄准。");
	text = text.replace("The blistering light is instantly blinding.", "炙热的阳光顿时让他感觉非常刺眼。");
	text = text.replace("Fark, I can\'t see shit.", "妈的，我看不见了。");
	text = text.replace("His aim wobbles as dark spots take over his vision.", "黑斑开始覆盖他的视线，他的瞄准变得摇摆不定。");
	text = text.replace("The arrow is loosed and sails wide of the sun. Real wide.", "弓箭丢失了它的目标，向着远离太阳的方向飞去。非常远。");
	text = text.replace("He looks at the company, eyes dimmed, hands out as he tries to steady himself while his sight returns.", "他看向自己的同伴，眼中一片模糊，不得不在视力恢复之前伸出手来保持平衡。");
	text = text.replace("Did I hit it?", "我击中它了吗？");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) hides his chuckling\./, "$1 停止了偷笑。");
	text = text.replace("Right on the button!", "正中靶心！");
	text = text.replace("The men burst into laughter.", "伙计们开始大笑起来。");

//hunt_food_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/As you help (.*?) get his boot out of the mud, (.*?) comes out of the bushes with what must be nearly a dozen rabbits strung together\./, "在你的帮助下 $1 把靴子从泥浆里抽了出来，$2 找到了那个挂着大约十二只兔子的灌木丛。");
	text = text.replace("He sets them down and starts to untie them.", "依次取下来，他开始把它们放在一起。");
	text = text.replace("The little bunnies - eyes wide, horrified in the end - all look quite tasty.", "那些小兔子－瞳孔放大，神色恐慌－看起来是那么的美味。");
	text = text.replace("The hunter grabs one by its neck and twists its body in a circle before pushing all its guts out in one swift motion.", "猎人拎起一只，抓住脖子，咔得一声扭了一圈，快速地开膛破肚，清理内脏。");
	text = text.replace("He repeats this process until every rabbit has been slaughtered.", "他重复着这个步骤，直到把所有兔子都处理干净。");
	text = text.replace(/As he wipes his hand on (.*?)\'s cloak, the hunter points to the mound of emptied bunnies at his feet\./, "接着，他在 $1的斗篷上擦了擦手，指了指地上那一堆已经处理好的兔子。");
	text = text.replace("That there is the eating pile.", "有一堆是吃的。");
	text = text.replace("He then points to the lump of rabbit guts.", "然后他指着那堆兔子内脏。");
	text = text.replace("That there is not the eating pile. Got it? Good.", "这一堆还不能吃，明白没？好的。");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) ran on ahead of the party a few hours ago and just now you catch back up to him\./, "$1 在队伍的前方行动了几个小时，不久前你刚刚赶上了他。");
	text = text.replace("He\'s standing with his foot on a dead deer, its chest punctured by a single arrow.", "他正踏在一只死掉的鹿身上，鹿的胸口上插着一只弓箭。");
	text = text.replace("As you approach, he grins and steps off.", "当你靠近时，他咧开嘴笑了笑，然后走了过来。");
	text = text.replace("He says if some of the brothers can help string it up he\'ll skin it and prep it.", "他说有没有兄弟来搭把手，挂一下这只鹿，我来把它剥一下皮，处理一下。");
	text = text.replace("Forest birds chitter and chatter above the company\'s march.", "战队在森林里鸟儿愉快的啼鸣中行进着。");
	text = text.replace("The sun winks between the canopy branches, a soft glint that peppers the ground with dots of light.", "太阳在头顶茂密的树梢中闪烁，一个个漏下来的光斑将地面晒地暖洋洋的。");
	text = text.replace("You spot a squirrel resting in one of the sun beams, enjoying the warmth as it gnaws on an acorn.", "你看见一只松鼠正在一道阳光中享受着温暖，一边啃着橡子一边休息。");
	text = text.replace("It stops, sensing you watching it, and then it suddenly jerks and a fleck of its blood meets your cheek.", "它停了下来，感觉到你在看着它，突然，它猛地一抖，几滴血飞溅到了你的脸上。");
	text = text.replace(/You wipe it away, turning back to see that the squirrel has been impaled by an arrow, every shrieking death throe quieter than the last as the volume of its life slowly turns down\. (.*?) suddenly breaks through the bushes with a bow in hand and a grin on his face\./, "你把它擦掉，回过头发现它已经被一支弓箭射穿，在这慢慢衰弱的生命之声面前，一切死亡时的哀嚎都好像变得那么得安静。$1 突然从树丛里窜出来，手里抓着他的弓，脸上带着笑。");
	text = text.replace("The hunter retrieves his kill and throws it in with a litter of others, a long hunter\'s line around which are tied all manner of critters foe and friend alike.", "猎人捡起他的收获，随手把它扔进了一堆其他的猎物之中－一捆串着各种敌对的，友善的生物的绳子中。");

//imprisoned_wildman_event.nut
	text = text.replace("While on the march, you come across a line of stopped wagons.", "在行军途中，你遇到一排停着的载重货车。");
	text = text.replace("You realize the wagons are cages with each serving a prison to a wild animal.", "你意识到这些载重货车是笼子，每一辆车都是为一只野生动物服务的。");
	text = text.replace("Touring the line of carts, you come to face a variety of beasts.", "浏览这一排货车，你遇到各种各样的野兽。");
	text = text.replace("A haunched and mewling black cat launches its mankiller claws through the bars.", "一只蹲着的，喵喵叫的黑猫从栅栏里伸出它的杀人魔爪。");
	text = text.replace("Jumping away, you back into another cage which violently rattles with a bear\'s roaring.", "你跳开，回到另一个笼子边，里面的熊在咆哮，发出刺耳的声音。");
	text = text.replace("Thankfully, its powerful paws are too fat to fit between the bars.", "值得庆幸的是，它强有力的爪子太胖了，塞不进栅栏里。");
	text = text.replace("Another cage sizzles with the hissing of snakes.", "另一个笼子发出蛇的嘶嘶声。");
	text = text.replace("A man leans back from behind one of the wagons.", "一个男人从一辆载重货车后面走出来，向后靠了靠。");
	text = text.replace("He\'s got a wild look on his face as though you\'d just caught him getting one off the wrist.", "他脸上的表情很野蛮，就好像你刚刚抓住了他的手腕一样。");
	text = text.replace("Hey! Who are you?", "嘿！你是谁？");
	text = text.replace("What are you doing here?", "你在这儿干什么？");
	text = text.replace(/You inform the stranger that you are the captain of the (.*?)\. The man straightens up\./, "你告诉那个陌生人你是 $1 的队长。男人直起身子。");
	text = text.replace("Oh, sellswords then! And I thought my luck had up and run off on me!", "噢，佣兵！我以为我的运气来了，跑到我身上去了！");
	text = text.replace("Look, I got a problem that my hired hands refused to help with.", "听着，我遇到了麻烦而我的雇工拒绝帮忙。");
	text = text.replace("They didn\'t care when they didn\'t know better, but the damn cloak fell off the wagon and then they just wouldn\'t shut up about how I wasn\'t paying them enough to transport such goods!", "他们漠不关心，也不想知道更多，但是现在该死的雇工们从载重货车上下来跑路了，然后雇主们闭口不谈我为他们运送了那么多货物！");
	
	text = text.replace("The animal tamer leads you to a carriage.", "驯兽者把你带到一辆马车前。");
	text = text.replace("You immediately see why his hired hands quit: a frenzied and mercurial wildman is sitting inside the cage.", "你马上就能看出他的雇工们逃跑的原因：一个疯狂而不可理喻的野人正坐在笼子里。");
	text = text.replace("Raw wrists bleed against his shackles, signs of attempted escapes.", "他的脚镣上有来自手腕的血迹，这是他企图逃跑的迹象。");
	text = text.replace("Half-starved, the wildman gnaws on sticks poking out from a tumbleweed of a beard.", "饿得半死的野人啃着一根棍状物，可能是风滚草的须子。");
	text = text.replace("Seeing this sad sight, you grab the stranger by his shirt and slam him against the wagon.", "看到这种悲伤的景象，你抓住陌生人的衬衫，把他往载重货车上撞。");
	text = text.replace("Does that look like an animal to you?", "你觉得那像动物吗？");
	text = text.replace("The animal tamer grins, ivory for teeth. He explains himself.", "驯兽者咧着嘴笑，露出用象牙做的假牙。他为自己辩解。");
	text = text.replace("Cityfolk have gotten wind of the \'uncivilized\' wildmen and wish to see them up close.", "市民们听到了“未开化”野人的风声，希望能近距离看到他们。");
	text = text.replace("I am only fulfilling this new demand as any businessman would.", "我只是像任何商人一样满足这个新需求。");
	text = text.replace("Now, all I need help with is to get that dead body out of the cage.", "现在，我只需要有人把那具尸体从笼子里弄出来。");
	text = text.replace("He points toward a corpse in the corner of the cage.", "他指着笼子角落里的一具尸体。");
	text = text.replace("The wildman rears back, snarling, and goes to protectively sit on the body.", "野人后退，咆哮着，走过去充满戒备地坐在尸体上。");
	text = text.replace("The animal tamer shakes his head.", "驯兽者摇了摇头。");
	text = text.replace("One of my helpers got too close and, well, yeah.", "我的一个助手靠得太近了，嗯，是的。");
	text = text.replace("I can\'t go into town with that mess in there so I thought maybe you could help me fish it out.", "我不能带着这些脏东西进城，所以我想你可以帮我把它弄出来。");
	text = text.replace("I\'ll pay plenty, of course.", "当然，我会付很多钱。");
	text = text.replace("A pouch of 250 crowns sound good to you?", "250克朗听起来不错吧？");
	text = text.replace("Just reach on in there and yank that garbage out.", "只要把手伸进去，把那个垃圾拉出来。");
	
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) is the one tasked with cleaning out the wildman\'s corpse-featured terrarium\./, "$1 接受了这个把尸体弄出野人杀人圈的任务。");
	text = text.replace("He rolls up his sleeves and approaches the cage with both hands out.", "他卷起袖子，双手伸向笼子。");
	text = text.replace("Whoa there, easy now. Easy!", "哇哦，这事简单。轻松！");
	text = text.replace("The wildman gets up off the dead body and goes to the other side of its habitat.", "野人从尸体上爬起来，走到笼子的另一边。");
	text = text.replace("The sellsword easily grabs the boot of the corpse and drags it toward the bars.", "佣兵很容易抓住尸体的靴子，把它拖向栅栏。");
	text = text.replace("It slips through with sickening ease, already clumped up in the fashion of discarded wet clothes.", "它以令人作呕的轻松方式滑过，已经像丢弃的湿衣服一样膨胀起来。");
	text = text.replace("Guts and limbs dribble off the edge of the wagon\'s platform.", "尸体的内脏和四肢从载重货车的平台边缘滚落下来。");
	text = text.replace("The animal tamer cheers happily.", "驯兽者高兴地欢呼。");
	text = text.replace("Thank you so much!", "非常感谢你！");
	text = text.replace("And you made it look so easy, too!", "你也让这事看起来很简单！");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) stares at the dead body with the realization that could have easily been him\./, "$1 盯着那具尸体，意识到自己差点就这个下场了。");
	text = text.replace("Yeah. You\'re welcome.", "好的。不客气。");
	
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) is tasked with getting the corpse out of the habitat\./, "$1 任务是把尸体弄出笼子。");
	text = text.replace("He approaches the cage like a harlot streetwalking a particularly pious town.", "他走近笼子，就像一个妓女在一个民风淳朴的小镇上游荡。");
	text = text.replace("When he gets close the bars, he smiles like an old friend.", "当他接近栅栏时，他笑得像野人的老朋友。");
	text = text.replace("Hey there buddy. That\'s a nice corpse you got there.", "嘿，老兄。你搞出来的尸体不错。");
	text = text.replace("A great corpse, truly one of the best I\'ve ever seen.", "一具伟大的尸体，真的是我见过的最好的尸体之一。");
	text = text.replace("How about I just... take it... out...", "不如我把…它拿…出来…");
	text = text.replace("When the mercenary reaches in, the wildman swipes out.", "当雇佣兵靠近时，野人就猛击上去。");
	text = text.replace(/It\'s too fast to even see\. (.*?) slowly turns around\./, "它的动作太快了，几乎看不到。$1 慢慢转身。");
	text = text.replace("There\'s a black hole where one of his eyes used to be.", "他原来的一只眼睛的成了一个黑洞。");
	text = text.replace("The wildman squishes the eye between his teeth, a white goop bursting forth like a popped pustule, and it turns into a filmy paste as he chews.", "野人把眼球压在牙缝里，一个白色的粘稠的东西像脓包一样冒出来，当他咀嚼的时候，它就变成了粘糊糊的东西。");
	text = text.replace("The animal tamer throws you a sack of crowns and runs off.", "驯兽者扔给你一袋钱，然后跑掉了。");
	text = text.replace("Not liable! I am not liable!", "不是我的错！不关我的事！");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) passes out as a few vengeful brothers stab the imprisoned wildman to death\./, "$1 晕了过去，几个复仇的兄弟刺死了被囚禁的野人。");
	text = text.replace("All the caged beasts roar up as though you\'d just slain their leader.", "所有关在笼子里的野兽都咆哮起来，好像你们刚刚杀了它们的首领。");
	text = text.replace("You quickly order the men away from the caravan before one of its beasts gets free and causes more damage.", "你赶紧命令队员们离开商队，以免其中一只野兽逃脱并造成更大的伤害。");
	
	text = text.replace("You tell this animal tamer that his problems are his own. He shrugs.", "你告诉这个驯兽者，这是他个人的问题。他耸耸肩。");
	text = text.replace("Yeah, I don\'t blame ya.", "是的，我没有怪你。");
	text = text.replace("You\'re smarter than you look, sellsword.", "你比你看起来更聪明，佣兵。");
	
	text = text.replace(/If anyone in the party could help talk the caged wildman down, it\'s probably (.*?)\. He goes to the cage, stares in\./, "如果队伍中有人能帮忙说服这个被关在笼子里的野人，那大概是 $1。他走向笼子，盯着里面。");
	text = text.replace("There\'s an exchange of hoots.", "他们开始交流。");
	text = text.replace("Your wildman raps the bars with a knuckle, and the prisoner raps back and hoots somberly.", "你的野人用指关节敲打着铁栅栏，而关在里面的那个则用手回击，并发出低沉的叫声。");
	text = text.replace(/Suddenly, (.*?) grabs the animal tamer by the head and drives him into the bars\./, "突然，$1 抓住驯兽者的头，把他赶进了笼子。");
	text = text.replace("You go to save the tamer, but the imprisoned wildman soars across the cage with atavistic terror in his eyes.", "你去救驯兽者，但被囚禁的野人在笼子里扑腾起来，眼睛里带着本能的恐惧。");
	text = text.replace("Stepping back for your own safety, you can only watch as this bestial man sets upon the tamer.", "你向后退却确保自身安全，你只能看着这个野人扑向驯兽者。");
	text = text.replace("Both wildmen pull and drag on the man\'s face.", "两个野人在他的脸上又拉又拽。");
	text = text.replace("The concussed man groggily yells.", "这个被打成脑震荡的家伙无力地大叫。");
	text = text.replace("I thought we had an agreeeeeemeeeaahh!", "我想我们达成共共共识了！");
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) corks his thumbs into the man\'s eyes while the imprisoned wildman grips the tamer\'s mouth and pulls down\./, "$1 把拇指塞进那人的眼睛里，而被囚禁的野人则抓住驯兽师的嘴巴往下拉。");
	text = text.replace("His head is literally ripped apart by the seams and sinews.", "他的头连筋带骨被撕裂了。");
	text = text.replace("A few men vomit as the tamer\'s brains falls out where his tongue should be, a truly awful way of speaking one\'s mind.", "当驯兽者的大脑从他的舌头原来的位置掉出来的时候，有几个人呕吐了，这真是一种表达个人的思想的可怕方式。");
	text = text.replace(/The \'warden\' taken care of, (.*?) looks at you and at the wildman with a sort of \'can we keep him\?\' gesture\./, "这个“看守”被解决了，$1 看着你，这个野人做出了“我们能收留他么？”的手势。");
	
	text = text.replace("An outstanding capacity for violence is well-suited to a mercenary band.", "对于一个雇佣兵团来说，在暴力方面的杰出才能是很必要的。");
	text = text.replace("You agree to take the imprisoned wildman on.", "你同意带走被囚禁的野人。");
	
	text = text.replace("You don\'t think the imprisoned wildman would fit in with the company, but you do set him free nonetheless.", "你不认为那个被囚禁的野人会适应战队，但你还是释放了他。");
	text = text.replace("He shoots out his cage like a banshee and runs for the tree line.", "他像女妖一样冲出笼子，向树林深处奔去。");
	text = text.replace("There he stands at a distance hooting and hollering until he runs off again.", "他站在远处，不断嚎叫，直到再次跑掉。");
	
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) the monk steps forward, hands clasped, head borrowed forward\./, "$1 这个僧侣走向前，双手合十，头向前倾。");
	text = text.replace("The embodiment of a sermon, the posture of good morals, or misguided ones.", "一副布道的做派，贤者的仪态，也可以说误入歧途的姿态。");
	text = text.replace("He pulls the tamer aside.", "他把驯兽者拉到一边。");
	text = text.replace("The old gods would frown upon what you have done here.", "汝之所为，神明不齿。");
	text = text.replace("The animal tamer laughs and leans against the cage, smugly crossing his arms.", "驯兽者笑着靠在笼子上，得意洋洋地交叉双臂。");
	text = text.replace("He states that the old gods consider slavery a part of the natural order. The monk continues.", "他说，古老神明认为奴隶制是自然秩序的一部分。这个僧侣继续道。");
	text = text.replace("True and it is by their grace that we are to make good use of our slaves.", "这是千真万确的，正是由于他们的恩典，我们才要好好地利用我们的奴隶。");
	text = text.replace("But this wildman is not kin to our way of life.", "但这个野人与我们的生活方式不同。");
	text = text.replace("You wish to enslave him by means of his being an outsider.", "你想奴役他个局外人。");
	text = text.replace("He does not understand the relationship which makes it especially grievous and improper.", "他不了解这种关系，这个事是不适当和特别令人痛苦的。");
	text = text.replace("My suggestion is to have him work for you and learn from you.", "我的建议是让他为你工作，向你学习。");
	text = text.replace("Make him a friend and you will have a friend for life-", "和他做朋友，你就会有一个终生的朋友－");
	text = text.replace("The imprisoned wildman\'s hands dart through the bars and digs his fingers into his eyeballs.", "被囚禁的野人把手穿过铁栅栏，手指插进了驯兽者的眼球。");
	text = text.replace(/His face is ripped apart like a loaf of old bread, a couple of coathangers for a jawbone, a tongue lolling like an uprooted snake\. (.*?) vomits as his face is doused in blood\. (.*?) shakes his head\./, "他的脸被撕开了，像一块旧面包，两根衣架套在一块颚骨上，舌头耷拉着，像一条被连根拔起的蛇。$1 满脸是血，吐了一地。$2 摇了摇头。");
	text = text.replace(/I\'d say he\'d fit right in with the (.*?)\.\.\./, "我想说他很适合 $1 …");
	
	text = text.replace(/Well, the animal tamer is gone and with him there\'s no one left to take care of the beasts\. (.*?) comes up and asks what should be done with them\./, "好吧，驯兽者走了，没有人跟他一起照顾这些野兽了。$1 上前询问应该如何处理它们。");
	
	text = text.replace("You feel it just wouldn\'t be right to leave them out here to starve to death and a caged creature no doubt has gamey meat when it comes to harvesting.", "你觉得把它们扔在这里饿死是不对的，毫无疑问，在这个丰收时节，这些关在笼子里的动物能够抓到野味的。");
	text = text.replace("You decide to let them on out of their cages.", "你决定让它们离开笼子。");
	text = text.replace("Most of these strange creatures make a beeline for the treeline, but two remain behind: a husky dog and a hooded falcon, both seemingly looking for a master.", "这些奇怪的动物大多径直朝树林走去，但有两只留在了后面：一只哈士奇和一只戴着兜帽的猎鹰，它们似乎都在寻找主人。");
	
	text = text.replace("It\'d be a crime to leave these animals out here to starve and rot.", "让这些动物在这里饿死腐烂掉是一种罪过。");
	text = text.replace("And it\'d also be a terrible waste of good meat.", "也是对肉食美味的一种可怕的浪费。");
	text = text.replace("You have the creatures slaughtered.", "你把那些动物都杀了。");
	text = text.replace("It\'s an easy, albeit brutal job, stabbing and slicing a bunch of hapless critters and beasts.", "这是一个简单的，但残酷的工作，刺和砍杀一群不幸的动物和野兽。");
	text = text.replace("The bear is the last to go, and it does not go easily.", "熊是最后一个死的，它不肯认命。");
	text = text.replace(/It manages to drag (.*?) close for a nasty swipe, but beyond that your men put it to a slow, grisly death\./, "它设法将 $1 拖近一顿猛揍，但除此之外，你的人把它慢慢地，残忍地杀死。");
	text = text.replace("The rest of the wagons are turned over and looted.", "其余的载重货车都被翻了个底朝天，被洗劫一空。");

//inadvertently_save_merchant_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/Walking about (.*?) with a few sellswords, you turn a corner to find an opulent man surrounded by thieves and bandits\./, "你带着几个佣兵在 $1 四处游荡，你转过一个街角，就会发现一个富商被盗贼和土匪包围着。");
	text = text.replace("They look over their shoulders and widen their eyes.", "他们环顾四周，怒目圆睁。");
	text = text.replace("One nicks the merchant on the cheek.", "其中一个在击打商人的面部。");
	text = text.replace("Alright, we\'ll get you next time ya bastard!", "好吧，下次我们会抓到你的，你这个混蛋！");
	text = text.replace("The scoundrels quickly make their leave.", "歹徒们很快离开了。");
	text = text.replace("A moment later and the merchant\'s heavily-armed guards appear.", "过了一会儿，商人的重装护卫出现了。");
	text = text.replace("Nursing his wound, he starts yelling at them.", "在包扎伤口时，商人大声训斥他们。");
	text = text.replace("What am I paying you for you sorry bastards?", "我不是给过你们这些欠骂的混蛋很多钱了么？");
	text = text.replace("The second I get into trouble and you\'re nowhere to be seen?", "我第二次遇到麻烦了，你们哪儿去了？");
	text = text.replace("Look at this man here, that\'s who I should be paying!", "看看这个人，这才是我应该付钱的人！");
	text = text.replace("Hey, take this for your troubles, stranger.", "嘿，给你添麻烦了，陌生人。");
	text = text.replace("The merchant throws you a satchel of crowns for your \'trouble,\' though all you did was turn a corner and run into a coincidence.", "商人丢给你一袋克朗，作为“麻烦”你的报酬，尽管你所做的一切只是拐了个弯，然后碰巧赶上了。");

//jousting_tournament_event.nut
	text = text.replace(/(.*?) comes to you with a paper in hand\./, "$1 手里拿着一张纸走过来。");
	text = text.replace("He slams it on your table and says he wishes to enter.", "他砰地一声把它摔到你的桌子上，说他想要参加。");
	text = text.replace("You pick up the scroll, unfurling it to show that a local town is hosting a jousting tournament.", "你拿起卷轴，展开它，看到当地一个小镇正在举办一场马术比赛。");
	text = text.replace("The man crosses his arms, awaiting your response.", "那人抱着肩，等待你的回答。");
	
	text = text.replace(/You agree to let (.*?) go to the tournament and, wanting to see it for yourself, you go along, too\./, "你同意 $1 去参加，同时自己也想亲眼看看，也就跟着去了。");
	text = text.replace("The jousting tourney crackles with energy as you near it.", "你刚走近赛场，比赛就发出剧烈的噼啪响声。");
	text = text.replace("Squires hurry to and fro, carrying great armfulls of armor and weapons, and some step slowly about with enormous lances hefted over their shoulders.", "扈从们抱着满怀的盔甲和武器，来回奔忙着，其中一些步伐缓慢，肩上扛着巨大的长矛。");
	text = text.replace("Other men brush very regal looking horses, many of which wear breastplates decorated with sigils.", "另一些人则骑着看起来非常高贵的马，不少都穿着饰有纹章的胸甲。");
	text = text.replace("In the distance, you listen to brief gallops, heavy hooves stamping roughshod and lumbering and then there\'s a snapping twang of wood on metal and cheers erupt.", "远处，你可以听到疾驰的风声，沉重的马蹄声，接着传来金属撞击木头的噼啪声，最后爆发出欢呼。");
	text = text.replace("As you look about the festivities, a nobleman walks up and stops you.", "当你环顾庆祝活动的时候，一个贵族走过来拦住了你。");
